1
00:00:20,400 --> 00:00:25,200
A long time ago in a galaxy far,
far away….

2
00:00:27,640 --> 00:00:34,160
STAR
WARS

3
00:00:38,680 --> 00:00:45,600
Episode IV
A NEW HOPE

4
00:00:46,920 --> 00:00:50,640
It is a period of civil war.

5
00:00:50,720 --> 00:00:54,920
Rebel spaceships, striking
from a hidden base, have won

6
00:00:55,000 --> 00:01:00,160
their first victory against
the evil Galactic Empire.

7
00:01:00,240 --> 00:01:05,280
During the battle, Rebel
spies managed to steal secret

8
00:01:05,360 --> 00:01:09,440
plans to the Empire's
ultimate weapon, the DEATH

9
00:01:09,520 --> 00:01:12,960
STAR, an armored space
station with enough power to

10
00:01:13,040 --> 00:01:16,040
destroy an entire planet.

11
00:01:16,120 --> 00:01:19,280
Pursued by the Empire's
sinister agents, Princess

12
00:01:19,360 --> 00:01:23,920
Leia races home aboard her
starship, custodian of the

13
00:01:24,000 --> 00:01:27,360
stolen plans that can save
her people and restore

14
00:01:27,440 --> 00:01:33,720
freedom to the galaxy....

15
00:02:46,640 --> 00:02:48,480
Did you hear that?

16
00:02:48,560 --> 00:02:51,840
They shut down the main reactor.
We'll be destroyed for sure.

17
00:02:51,920 --> 00:02:53,040
This is madness.

18
00:03:03,520 --> 00:03:05,320
We're doomed.

19
00:03:07,040 --> 00:03:09,120
There'll be no escape
for the princess this time.

20
00:03:12,240 --> 00:03:13,720
What's that?

21
00:04:56,400 --> 00:04:58,880
R2-D2, where are you?

22
00:05:15,240 --> 00:05:17,800
At last. Where have you been?

23
00:05:17,920 --> 00:05:21,040
They're heading in this direction.
What are we going to do?

24
00:05:21,120 --> 00:05:25,640
We'll be sent to the Kessel spice mines
or smashed into who knows what.

25
00:05:25,760 --> 00:05:28,320
Wait a minute. Where are you going?

26
00:05:40,760 --> 00:05:43,360
The Death Star plans
are not in the main computer.

27
00:05:43,880 --> 00:05:46,080
Where are those transmissions
you intercepted?

28
00:05:46,600 --> 00:05:49,200
What have you done with those plans?

29
00:05:49,280 --> 00:05:51,680
We intercepted no transmissions.

30
00:05:52,080 --> 00:05:56,200
This is a consular ship.
We're on a diplomatic mission.

31
00:05:56,280 --> 00:06:00,640
If this is a consular ship,
where is the ambassador?

32
00:06:04,280 --> 00:06:07,760
Commander, tear this ship apart
until you've found those plans!

33
00:06:07,840 --> 00:06:10,640
And bring me the passengers!
I want them alive!

34
00:06:23,360 --> 00:06:24,800
There's one. Set for stun.

35
00:06:30,640 --> 00:06:31,960
She'll be all right.

36
00:06:32,040 --> 00:06:34,160
Inform Lord Vader we have a prisoner.

37
00:06:35,680 --> 00:06:38,440
Hey. You're not permitted in there.
It's restricted.

38
00:06:38,520 --> 00:06:40,160
You'll be deactivated for sure.

39
00:06:42,280 --> 00:06:44,960
Don't call me a mindless philosopher,
you overweight glob of grease.

40
00:06:45,040 --> 00:06:46,560
Come out, before somebody sees you.

41
00:06:49,000 --> 00:06:51,240
Secret mission? What plans?

42
00:06:51,320 --> 00:06:53,920
What are you talking about?
I'm not getting in there.

43
00:06:57,160 --> 00:06:58,480
I'm going to regret this.

44
00:07:06,680 --> 00:07:10,080
-There goes another one.
-Hold your fire. There's no life-forms.

45
00:07:10,160 --> 00:07:11,480
It must have short-circuited.

46
00:07:11,560 --> 00:07:15,520
That's funny. The damage
doesn't look as bad from out here.

47
00:07:17,160 --> 00:07:19,160
Are you sure this thing is safe?

48
00:07:38,080 --> 00:07:40,680
Darth Vader. Only you could be so bold.

49
00:07:40,760 --> 00:07:43,000
The Imperial Senate
will not sit still for this.

50
00:07:43,080 --> 00:07:44,400
When they hear
you've attacked a diplomatic...

51
00:07:44,480 --> 00:07:46,560
Don't act so surprised, Your Highness.

52
00:07:46,640 --> 00:07:48,880
You weren't on
any mercy mission this time.

53
00:07:48,960 --> 00:07:52,720
Several transmissions were beamed
to this ship by rebel spies.

54
00:07:52,800 --> 00:07:55,800
I want to know what happened
to the plans they sent you.

55
00:07:55,880 --> 00:07:57,720
I don't know what you're talking about.

56
00:07:57,800 --> 00:08:00,880
I'm a member of the Imperial Senate
on a diplomatic mission to Alderaan.

57
00:08:00,960 --> 00:08:03,840
You are part of the Rebel Alliance
and a traitor.

58
00:08:04,400 --> 00:08:06,400
Take her away!

59
00:08:10,120 --> 00:08:11,520
Holding her is dangerous.

60
00:08:11,600 --> 00:08:15,160
If word of this gets out, it could generate
sympathy for the rebellion in the senate.

61
00:08:15,240 --> 00:08:17,920
I have traced the rebel spies to her.

62
00:08:18,000 --> 00:08:20,760
Now she is my only link
to finding their secret base.

63
00:08:20,840 --> 00:08:22,560
She'll die before she'll tell you anything.

64
00:08:22,640 --> 00:08:24,320
Leave that to me.

65
00:08:24,400 --> 00:08:27,920
Send a distress signal, and then inform
the senate that all aboard were killed.

66
00:08:28,000 --> 00:08:31,200
Lord Vader, the battle station plans
are not aboard this ship

67
00:08:31,280 --> 00:08:32,760
and no transmissions were made.

68
00:08:33,200 --> 00:08:35,400
An escape pod was jettisoned
during the fighting,

69
00:08:35,480 --> 00:08:36,880
but no life-forms were aboard.

70
00:08:37,600 --> 00:08:40,080
She must have hidden
the plans in the escape pod.

71
00:08:40,200 --> 00:08:41,760
Send a detachment
down to retrieve them.

72
00:08:41,840 --> 00:08:43,800
See to it personally, Commander.

73
00:08:43,880 --> 00:08:45,800
There'll be no one to stop us this time.

74
00:08:45,920 --> 00:08:47,480
Yes, sir.

75
00:09:02,120 --> 00:09:04,120
How did we get into this mess?

76
00:09:04,200 --> 00:09:06,640
I really don't know how.

77
00:09:07,160 --> 00:09:11,120
We seem to be made to suffer.
It's our lot in life.

78
00:09:13,200 --> 00:09:17,440
I've got to rest before I fall apart.
My joints are almost frozen.

79
00:09:23,720 --> 00:09:25,880
What a desolate place this is.

80
00:09:30,520 --> 00:09:32,160
Where do you think you're going?

81
00:09:32,240 --> 00:09:33,680
Well, I'm not going that way.

82
00:09:34,440 --> 00:09:36,440
It's much too rocky.

83
00:09:36,520 --> 00:09:38,440
This way is much easier.

84
00:09:38,520 --> 00:09:40,960
What makes you think
there are settlements over there?

85
00:09:42,920 --> 00:09:44,440
Don't get technical with me.

86
00:09:45,720 --> 00:09:47,840
What mission?
What are you talking about?

87
00:09:50,000 --> 00:09:52,920
I've just about had enough of you.

88
00:09:53,000 --> 00:09:54,240
Go that way.

89
00:09:54,360 --> 00:09:58,000
You'll be malfunctioning within a day,
you nearsighted scrap pile.

90
00:09:58,080 --> 00:10:00,000
And don't let me catch you
following me, begging for help

91
00:10:00,080 --> 00:10:02,000
because you won't get it.

92
00:10:16,000 --> 00:10:17,520
No more adventures.

93
00:10:17,600 --> 00:10:19,680
I'm not going that way.

94
00:10:53,680 --> 00:10:56,680
That malfunctioning little twerp.
This is all his fault.

95
00:10:57,680 --> 00:10:59,800
He tricked me into going this way,

96
00:10:59,880 --> 00:11:01,800
but he'll do no better.

97
00:11:05,400 --> 00:11:07,280
Wait. What's that?

98
00:11:07,360 --> 00:11:10,200
A transport. I'm saved.

99
00:11:10,280 --> 00:11:12,000
Over here!

100
00:11:12,080 --> 00:11:14,680
Hey! Hey!

101
00:11:14,760 --> 00:11:18,240
Help! Please help!

102
00:14:49,280 --> 00:14:50,280
R2?

103
00:14:53,920 --> 00:14:57,760
R2-D2, it is you! It is you!

104
00:15:31,280 --> 00:15:35,280
Someone was in the pod.
The tracks go off in this direction.

105
00:15:35,360 --> 00:15:37,280
Look, sir. Droids.

106
00:15:52,040 --> 00:15:53,280
We stopped.

107
00:15:53,360 --> 00:15:55,120
Wake up. Wake up!

108
00:16:02,040 --> 00:16:03,680
We're doomed.

109
00:16:11,960 --> 00:16:12,960
Do you think they'll melt us down?

110
00:16:26,800 --> 00:16:29,000
Don't shoot. Don't shoot.

111
00:16:29,080 --> 00:16:31,200
Will this never end?

112
00:17:10,560 --> 00:17:13,400
-Fine. Let's go.
-Luke!

113
00:17:13,480 --> 00:17:15,000
Luke!

114
00:17:18,520 --> 00:17:23,560
Luke, tell your uncle if he gets
a translator, be sure it speaks Bocce.

115
00:17:23,640 --> 00:17:26,080
Doesn't look like we have much choice,
but I'll remind him.

116
00:17:37,200 --> 00:17:39,400
Yeah, we'll take that red one.

117
00:17:39,480 --> 00:17:41,440
No, not that one.

118
00:17:43,240 --> 00:17:46,280
You. I suppose you're programmed
for etiquette and protocol.

119
00:17:46,360 --> 00:17:50,320
Protocol? It's my primary function, sir.
I am well-versed in all the customs...

120
00:17:50,400 --> 00:17:53,760
-I have no need for a protocol droid.
-Of course you haven't, sir.

121
00:17:53,880 --> 00:17:56,560
Not in an environment such as this.
That's why I have been programmed...

122
00:17:56,640 --> 00:18:00,680
I need a droid who understands the
binary language of moisture vaporators.

123
00:18:00,760 --> 00:18:04,080
Vaporators? Sir, my first job
was programming binary load lifters,

124
00:18:04,160 --> 00:18:06,280
very similar to your vaporators
in most respects.

125
00:18:06,360 --> 00:18:10,000
-Can you speak Bocce?
-Of course. It's like a second language.

126
00:18:10,080 --> 00:18:12,240
-All right. Shut up. I'll take this one.
-Shutting up, sir.

127
00:18:12,320 --> 00:18:13,520
Luke!

128
00:18:15,800 --> 00:18:18,640
Take these two to the garage.
I want them cleaned up before dinner.

129
00:18:18,720 --> 00:18:21,640
But I was going into Tosche Station
to pick up some power converters.

130
00:18:21,720 --> 00:18:23,960
You can waste time with your friends
when your chores are done.

131
00:18:24,080 --> 00:18:25,800
Now come on. Get to it.

132
00:18:27,680 --> 00:18:28,960
All right. Come on.

133
00:18:31,640 --> 00:18:34,080
And the red one. Come on.

134
00:18:34,800 --> 00:18:36,800
Come on, red. Let's go.

135
00:18:56,440 --> 00:18:58,440
-Uncle Owen.
-Yeah?

136
00:18:58,520 --> 00:19:01,240
This R2 unit has a bad motivator. Look.

137
00:19:01,600 --> 00:19:03,680
Hey, what are you trying to push on us?

138
00:19:06,680 --> 00:19:11,640
Excuse me, sir, but that R2 unit
is in prime condition, a real bargain.

139
00:19:11,720 --> 00:19:14,320
Uncle Owen, what about that one?

140
00:19:14,400 --> 00:19:17,760
What about that blue one?
We'll take that one.

141
00:19:17,880 --> 00:19:18,880
Take this away.

142
00:19:18,960 --> 00:19:20,480
You'll be pleased with that one, sir.

143
00:19:20,560 --> 00:19:24,000
He really is in first-class condition.
I've worked with him before.

144
00:19:24,080 --> 00:19:25,520
Here he comes.

145
00:19:28,800 --> 00:19:30,520
Okay. Let's go.

146
00:19:30,600 --> 00:19:32,040
Don't you forget this.

147
00:19:32,120 --> 00:19:35,640
Why I should stick my neck out for you
is quite beyond my capacity.

148
00:19:41,800 --> 00:19:45,120
Thank the maker.
This oil bath is going to feel so good.

149
00:19:46,560 --> 00:19:50,200
I've got such a bad case of
dust contamination, I can barely move.

150
00:19:50,280 --> 00:19:51,840
It just isn't fair.

151
00:19:51,920 --> 00:19:55,080
Biggs is right.
I'm never gonna get out of here.

152
00:19:55,160 --> 00:19:57,360
Is there anything I might do to help?

153
00:19:57,440 --> 00:20:00,880
No, not unless you can alter time,
speed up the harvest,

154
00:20:00,960 --> 00:20:02,400
or teleport me off this rock.

155
00:20:02,480 --> 00:20:04,040
I don't think so, sir.

156
00:20:04,120 --> 00:20:07,200
I'm only a droid and not very
knowledgeable about such things.

157
00:20:07,280 --> 00:20:09,200
Not on this planet, anyway.

158
00:20:09,280 --> 00:20:12,720
As a matter of fact,
I'm not even sure which planet I'm on.

159
00:20:12,800 --> 00:20:14,880
Well, if there's a bright center
to the universe,

160
00:20:14,960 --> 00:20:17,200
you're on the planet
that it's farthest from.

161
00:20:17,280 --> 00:20:19,720
I see, sir.

162
00:20:19,800 --> 00:20:22,640
-You can call me Luke.
-I see, Sir Luke.

163
00:20:23,760 --> 00:20:25,240
Just Luke.

164
00:20:25,880 --> 00:20:29,120
And I am C-3PO,
human-cyborg relations.

165
00:20:29,200 --> 00:20:31,800
And this is my counterpart, R2-D2.

166
00:20:31,880 --> 00:20:33,200
Hello.

167
00:20:34,520 --> 00:20:36,520
You got a lot of carbon scoring here.

168
00:20:36,600 --> 00:20:38,160
Looks like you boys
have seen a lot of action.

169
00:20:38,240 --> 00:20:39,400
With all we've been through,

170
00:20:39,480 --> 00:20:41,680
sometimes I'm amazed
we're in as good condition as we are,

171
00:20:41,760 --> 00:20:43,440
what with the rebellion and all.

172
00:20:43,520 --> 00:20:45,320
You know of the rebellion
against the Empire?

173
00:20:45,400 --> 00:20:46,800
That's how we came to be
in your service,

174
00:20:46,880 --> 00:20:49,000
if you take my meaning, sir.

175
00:20:49,080 --> 00:20:51,440
-Have you been in many battles?
-Several, I think.

176
00:20:51,520 --> 00:20:53,440
There's not much to tell.

177
00:20:53,560 --> 00:20:57,160
I'm not much more than an interpreter
and not very good at telling stories.

178
00:20:57,240 --> 00:21:00,360
Well, not at making them
interesting, anyway.

179
00:21:00,440 --> 00:21:02,360
Well, my little friend,

180
00:21:02,440 --> 00:21:04,520
you got something jammed
in here real good.

181
00:21:04,600 --> 00:21:06,080
Were you on a Starcruiser or...

182
00:21:06,920 --> 00:21:10,000
<i>Help me, Obi-Wan Kenobi.</i>
<i>You're my only hope.</i>

183
00:21:10,080 --> 00:21:11,800
What's this?

184
00:21:11,880 --> 00:21:14,960
"What is what"?
He asked you a question. What is that?

185
00:21:15,080 --> 00:21:19,040
<i>Help me, Obi-Wan Kenobi.</i>
<i>You're my only hope.</i>

186
00:21:22,400 --> 00:21:26,320
<i>Help me, Obi-Wan Kenobi.</i>
<i>You're my only hope.</i>

187
00:21:28,840 --> 00:21:30,840
He says it's nothing, sir,
merely a malfunction.

188
00:21:30,920 --> 00:21:33,000
Old data. Pay it no mind.

189
00:21:33,080 --> 00:21:35,520
Who is she? She's beautiful.

190
00:21:35,600 --> 00:21:38,960
I'm afraid I'm not quite sure, sir.

191
00:21:39,040 --> 00:21:41,280
I think she was a passenger
on our last voyage.

192
00:21:41,360 --> 00:21:43,520
A person of some importance, I believe.

193
00:21:43,600 --> 00:21:45,800
-Our captain was...
-Is there any more to this recording?

194
00:21:47,960 --> 00:21:51,160
Behave yourself, R2.
You're going to get us into trouble.

195
00:21:51,240 --> 00:21:54,000
It's all right. You can trust him.
He's our new master.

196
00:21:54,120 --> 00:21:55,720
<i>You're my only hope.</i>

197
00:21:57,120 --> 00:22:00,200
He says he's the property
of Obi-Wan Kenobi,

198
00:22:00,280 --> 00:22:01,760
a resident of these parts,

199
00:22:01,880 --> 00:22:03,560
and it's a private message for him.

200
00:22:03,640 --> 00:22:05,760
Frankly, I don't know
what he's talking about.

201
00:22:05,840 --> 00:22:07,840
Our last master was Captain Antilles.

202
00:22:07,920 --> 00:22:12,480
But with all we've been through,
this R2 unit has become a bit eccentric.

203
00:22:13,040 --> 00:22:15,960
Obi-Wan Kenobi.
I wonder if he means old Ben Kenobi.

204
00:22:16,040 --> 00:22:18,600
I beg your pardon, sir, but do you know
what he's talking about?

205
00:22:18,680 --> 00:22:21,120
I don't know anyone named Obi-Wan,

206
00:22:21,880 --> 00:22:24,040
but old Ben lives out
beyond the Dune Sea.

207
00:22:24,120 --> 00:22:25,960
He's kind of a strange old hermit.

208
00:22:27,120 --> 00:22:29,120
I wonder who she is.

209
00:22:29,240 --> 00:22:32,280
Sounds like she's in trouble.
I better play back the whole thing.

210
00:22:35,760 --> 00:22:39,200
He says the restraining bolt has
short-circuited his recording system.

211
00:22:39,600 --> 00:22:41,640
He suggests that if you remove the bolt,

212
00:22:41,720 --> 00:22:44,640
he might be able to play back
the entire recording.

213
00:22:44,720 --> 00:22:47,080
Oh, yeah. Well...

214
00:22:47,160 --> 00:22:50,720
I guess you're too small
to run away on me if I take this off.

215
00:22:50,800 --> 00:22:51,960
Okay.

216
00:22:54,720 --> 00:22:56,320
There you go.

217
00:22:58,000 --> 00:23:01,600
Where'd she go? Bring her back.
Play back the entire message.

218
00:23:01,680 --> 00:23:02,640
"What message"?

219
00:23:03,440 --> 00:23:04,880
The one you've just been playing.

220
00:23:04,960 --> 00:23:07,080
The one you're carrying
inside your rusty innards.

221
00:23:07,160 --> 00:23:09,560
Luke! Luke!

222
00:23:09,640 --> 00:23:11,840
I'll be right there, Aunt Beru.

223
00:23:11,920 --> 00:23:15,120
I'm sorry, sir, but he appears to have
picked up a slight flutter.

224
00:23:15,200 --> 00:23:18,640
Here. See what you can do with him.
I'll be right back.

225
00:23:21,280 --> 00:23:24,120
Just you reconsider
playing that message for him.

226
00:23:25,280 --> 00:23:27,640
No, I don't think he likes you at all.

227
00:23:27,760 --> 00:23:30,000
No, I don't like you either.

228
00:23:38,840 --> 00:23:41,600
I think that R2 unit
might have been stolen.

229
00:23:41,680 --> 00:23:42,800
What makes you think that?

230
00:23:42,880 --> 00:23:45,480
I stumbled across a recording
while I was cleaning him.

231
00:23:45,560 --> 00:23:48,320
He says he belongs to someone
called Obi-Wan Kenobi.

232
00:23:50,880 --> 00:23:54,240
I thought he might have meant old Ben.
Do you know what he's talking about?

233
00:23:56,960 --> 00:23:58,520
I wonder if he's related to Ben.

234
00:23:58,600 --> 00:24:00,400
That wizard's just a crazy old man.

235
00:24:02,000 --> 00:24:03,640
Tomorrow, take that R2 unit
to Anchorhead

236
00:24:03,720 --> 00:24:05,360
and have its memory erased.

237
00:24:05,440 --> 00:24:07,600
That'll be the end of it.
It belongs to us now.

238
00:24:09,360 --> 00:24:12,400
But what if this Obi-Wan
comes looking for him?

239
00:24:12,480 --> 00:24:14,240
He won't.

240
00:24:14,320 --> 00:24:16,320
I don't think he exists anymore.

241
00:24:16,400 --> 00:24:18,160
He died about the same time
as your father.

242
00:24:18,600 --> 00:24:21,280
-He knew my father?
-I told you to forget it.

243
00:24:22,400 --> 00:24:26,000
Your only concern is to prepare
those new droids for tomorrow.

244
00:24:26,080 --> 00:24:27,680
In the morning,
I want them on the south ridge,

245
00:24:27,760 --> 00:24:29,840
working on those condensers.

246
00:24:29,920 --> 00:24:31,400
Yes, sir.

247
00:24:32,760 --> 00:24:35,320
I think those new droids
are gonna work out fine.

248
00:24:35,400 --> 00:24:38,960
In fact, I was also thinking
about our agreement,

249
00:24:39,040 --> 00:24:40,800
about me staying on another season.

250
00:24:43,200 --> 00:24:46,520
If these new droids work out,
I want to apply to the academy this year.

251
00:24:47,440 --> 00:24:49,400
You mean the next semester
before the harvest?

252
00:24:49,480 --> 00:24:51,400
Sure. There's more than enough droids.

253
00:24:51,480 --> 00:24:53,520
Harvest is when I need you the most.

254
00:24:53,600 --> 00:24:55,560
It's only one season more.

255
00:24:55,680 --> 00:24:58,840
This year we'll make enough
on the harvest to hire more hands

256
00:24:58,920 --> 00:25:01,200
and then you can go
to the academy next year.

257
00:25:02,160 --> 00:25:04,160
You must understand
I need you here, Luke.

258
00:25:04,240 --> 00:25:07,200
-But it's a whole 'nother year.
-It's only one more season.

259
00:25:07,280 --> 00:25:09,360
That's what you said
when Biggs and Tank left.

260
00:25:09,440 --> 00:25:11,880
-Where are you going?
-Looks like I'm going nowhere.

261
00:25:11,960 --> 00:25:13,880
I have to go finish
cleaning those droids.

262
00:25:13,960 --> 00:25:17,560
Owen, he can't stay here forever.
Most of his friends have gone.

263
00:25:17,640 --> 00:25:19,880
It means so much to him.

264
00:25:19,960 --> 00:25:22,480
I'll make it up to him next year.
I promise.

265
00:25:24,160 --> 00:25:28,160
Luke's just not a farmer, Owen.
He has too much of his father in him.

266
00:25:28,600 --> 00:25:30,400
That's what I'm afraid of.

267
00:26:19,600 --> 00:26:22,760
-What are you doing hiding back there?
-It wasn't my fault, sir.

268
00:26:22,840 --> 00:26:24,640
Please don't deactivate me.

269
00:26:24,720 --> 00:26:27,440
I told him not to go,
but he's faulty, malfunctioning.

270
00:26:27,560 --> 00:26:30,760
-Kept babbling on about his mission.
-Oh, no.

271
00:26:39,200 --> 00:26:41,600
That R2 unit has
always been a problem.

272
00:26:42,000 --> 00:26:44,280
These astro droids
are getting quite out of hand.

273
00:26:44,360 --> 00:26:46,560
Even I can't understand
their logic at times.

274
00:26:46,640 --> 00:26:49,360
How could I be so stupid?
He's nowhere in sight.

275
00:26:49,840 --> 00:26:50,880
Blast it!

276
00:26:50,960 --> 00:26:53,200
Pardon me, sir,
but couldn't we go after him?

277
00:26:53,280 --> 00:26:54,800
It's too dangerous
with the Sandpeople around.

278
00:26:54,880 --> 00:26:56,440
We'll have to wait till morning.

279
00:26:56,520 --> 00:26:58,520
Luke, I'm shutting the power down.

280
00:26:58,600 --> 00:27:01,160
I'll be there in a few minutes.

281
00:27:01,240 --> 00:27:03,640
Boy, am I gonna get it.

282
00:27:03,720 --> 00:27:05,840
That little droid's gonna cause me
a lot of trouble.

283
00:27:05,920 --> 00:27:07,880
He excels at that, sir.

284
00:27:08,960 --> 00:27:10,480
Come on.

285
00:27:30,560 --> 00:27:32,480
Have you seen Luke this morning?

286
00:27:32,560 --> 00:27:36,000
He said he had things to do before
he started today, so he left early.

287
00:27:36,080 --> 00:27:39,760
-Did he take those new droids with him?
-I think so.

288
00:27:39,840 --> 00:27:42,640
He better have those units in
the south range repaired by midday

289
00:27:42,760 --> 00:27:44,400
or there'll be hell to pay.

290
00:27:45,400 --> 00:27:48,000
There's a droid on the scanner.
Dead ahead.

291
00:27:48,080 --> 00:27:51,080
It might be our little R2 unit.
Hit the accelerator.

292
00:28:13,920 --> 00:28:16,400
Where do you think you're going?

293
00:28:16,480 --> 00:28:18,400
Master Luke is your rightful owner now.

294
00:28:18,480 --> 00:28:21,440
We'll have no more
of this Obi-Wan Kenobi gibberish.

295
00:28:22,720 --> 00:28:24,360
Don't talk to me of your mission either.

296
00:28:24,440 --> 00:28:27,520
You're fortunate he doesn't blast you
into a million pieces right here.

297
00:28:27,640 --> 00:28:30,480
No. It's all right,
but I think we'd better go.

298
00:28:31,120 --> 00:28:32,320
What's wrong with him now?

299
00:28:33,160 --> 00:28:35,560
There are several creatures
approaching from the southeast.

300
00:28:36,120 --> 00:28:38,600
Sandpeople. Or worse.

301
00:28:39,960 --> 00:28:41,600
Come on. Let's go have a look.

302
00:28:41,680 --> 00:28:42,760
Come on.

303
00:28:45,480 --> 00:28:49,280
Well, there are two Banthas down there,
but I don't see any...

304
00:28:49,360 --> 00:28:51,160
Wait a second.

305
00:28:51,240 --> 00:28:53,640
They're Sandpeople, all right.
I can see one of them now.

306
00:30:08,720 --> 00:30:09,880
Hello there.

307
00:30:12,560 --> 00:30:16,240
Come here, my little friend.
Don't be afraid.

308
00:30:18,440 --> 00:30:20,080
Don't worry. He'll be all right.

309
00:30:26,240 --> 00:30:28,800
Rest easy, son. You've had a busy day.

310
00:30:29,600 --> 00:30:32,480
You're fortunate to be all in one piece.

311
00:30:35,800 --> 00:30:38,080
Ben? Ben Kenobi?

312
00:30:38,160 --> 00:30:40,160
Boy, am I glad to see you.

313
00:30:40,240 --> 00:30:43,280
The Jundland Wastes
are not to be traveled lightly.

314
00:30:46,480 --> 00:30:50,640
Tell me, young Luke,
what brings you out this far?

315
00:30:50,720 --> 00:30:52,240
This little droid.

316
00:30:54,360 --> 00:30:56,000
I think he's searching
for his former master,

317
00:30:56,080 --> 00:30:58,240
but I've never seen
such devotion in a droid before.

318
00:31:00,200 --> 00:31:03,320
He claims to be the property
of an Obi-Wan Kenobi.

319
00:31:03,400 --> 00:31:06,000
Is he a relative of yours?
Do you know who he's talking about?

320
00:31:07,520 --> 00:31:09,160
Obi-Wan Kenobi?

321
00:31:11,600 --> 00:31:13,520
Obi-Wan.

322
00:31:14,000 --> 00:31:18,200
Now, that's a name
I've not heard in a long time.

323
00:31:18,800 --> 00:31:20,640
A long time.

324
00:31:21,800 --> 00:31:24,720
I think my uncle knows him.
He said he was dead.

325
00:31:24,800 --> 00:31:26,680
He's not dead.

326
00:31:26,760 --> 00:31:27,840
Not yet.

327
00:31:28,240 --> 00:31:31,480
-You know him?
-Of course I know him.

328
00:31:31,560 --> 00:31:32,880
He's me.

329
00:31:35,040 --> 00:31:38,360
I haven't gone by the name of Obi-Wan

330
00:31:38,440 --> 00:31:41,080
since before you were born.

331
00:31:41,160 --> 00:31:42,800
Then the droid does belong to you.

332
00:31:43,200 --> 00:31:45,520
I don't seem to remember
ever owning a droid.

333
00:31:47,760 --> 00:31:49,520
Very interesting.

334
00:31:50,880 --> 00:31:53,400
I think we better get indoors.

335
00:31:53,480 --> 00:31:56,200
The Sandpeople are easily startled,

336
00:31:56,280 --> 00:31:59,080
but they'll soon be back,
and in greater numbers.

337
00:32:02,040 --> 00:32:03,360
3PO.

338
00:32:12,720 --> 00:32:15,400
Where am I?
I must have taken a bad step.

339
00:32:17,360 --> 00:32:20,120
Can you stand? We've gotta get out
of here before the Sandpeople return.

340
00:32:20,200 --> 00:32:22,960
I don't think I can make it.
You go on, Master Luke.

341
00:32:23,040 --> 00:32:27,120
There's no sense in you risking yourself
on my account. I'm done for.

342
00:32:28,080 --> 00:32:30,040
No, you're not. What kind of talk is that?

343
00:32:30,120 --> 00:32:32,040
Quickly. They're on the move.

344
00:32:37,280 --> 00:32:40,720
My father didn't fight in the wars.
He was a navigator on a spice freighter.

345
00:32:40,800 --> 00:32:44,560
That's what your uncle told you.
He didn't hold with your father's ideals.

346
00:32:44,640 --> 00:32:47,720
Thought he should have stayed here
and not gotten involved.

347
00:32:48,440 --> 00:32:50,800
-You fought in the Clone Wars?
-Yes.

348
00:32:51,280 --> 00:32:54,920
I was once a Jedi knight,
the same as your father.

349
00:32:57,320 --> 00:32:58,680
I wish I'd known him.

350
00:32:58,760 --> 00:33:01,480
He was the best starpilot in the galaxy

351
00:33:02,560 --> 00:33:04,440
and a cunning warrior.

352
00:33:04,520 --> 00:33:07,400
I understand you've become
quite a good pilot yourself.

353
00:33:09,280 --> 00:33:11,600
And he was a good friend.

354
00:33:12,280 --> 00:33:13,360
Which reminds me...

355
00:33:14,440 --> 00:33:16,440
I have something here for you.

356
00:33:18,560 --> 00:33:21,160
Your father wanted you to have this
when you were old enough,

357
00:33:21,680 --> 00:33:23,800
but your uncle wouldn't allow it.

358
00:33:24,760 --> 00:33:26,920
He feared you might follow old Obi-Wan

359
00:33:27,000 --> 00:33:30,480
on some damn-fool idealistic crusade,
like your father did.

360
00:33:30,920 --> 00:33:33,480
Sir, if you'll not be needing me,
I'll close down for a while.

361
00:33:33,560 --> 00:33:35,120
Sure. Go ahead.

362
00:33:37,800 --> 00:33:41,200
-What is it?
-Your father's lightsaber.

363
00:33:42,000 --> 00:33:43,600
This is the weapon of a Jedi knight.

364
00:33:44,640 --> 00:33:47,800
Not as clumsy or random as a blaster.

365
00:33:48,480 --> 00:33:50,800
An elegant weapon

366
00:33:50,880 --> 00:33:53,840
for a more civilized age.

367
00:33:55,680 --> 00:33:58,120
For over a thousand generations,
the Jedi knights

368
00:33:58,200 --> 00:34:02,240
were the guardians of
peace and justice in the old Republic

369
00:34:02,760 --> 00:34:05,160
before the dark times,

370
00:34:05,240 --> 00:34:06,840
before the Empire.

371
00:34:10,000 --> 00:34:11,720
How did my father die?

372
00:34:14,160 --> 00:34:16,760
A young Jedi named Darth Vader,

373
00:34:16,840 --> 00:34:19,360
who was a pupil of mine
until he turned to evil

374
00:34:20,200 --> 00:34:23,520
helped the Empire hunt down
and destroy the Jedi knights.

375
00:34:25,320 --> 00:34:27,720
He betrayed and murdered your father.

376
00:34:29,480 --> 00:34:31,840
Now the Jedi are all but extinct.

377
00:34:33,040 --> 00:34:36,800
Vader was seduced
by the dark side of the Force.

378
00:34:37,560 --> 00:34:39,680
The Force?

379
00:34:39,760 --> 00:34:42,800
The Force is
what gives a Jedi his power.

380
00:34:42,880 --> 00:34:45,400
It's an energy field
created by all living things.

381
00:34:45,520 --> 00:34:48,080
It surrounds us and penetrates us.

382
00:34:48,160 --> 00:34:50,240
It binds the galaxy together.

383
00:34:57,200 --> 00:34:59,840
Let's see if we can't figure out
what you are, my little friend,

384
00:35:01,040 --> 00:35:03,200
and where you come from.

385
00:35:03,280 --> 00:35:06,440
-I saw part of a message...
-I seem to have found it.

386
00:35:06,520 --> 00:35:10,880
<i>General Kenobi, years ago you served</i>
<i>my father in the Clone Wars.</i>

387
00:35:11,240 --> 00:35:14,400
<i>Now he begs you to help him</i>
<i>in his struggle against the Empire.</i>

388
00:35:14,480 --> 00:35:17,840
<i>I regret that I am unable to present</i>
<i>my father's request in person.</i>

389
00:35:17,920 --> 00:35:19,560
<i>But my ship has fallen under attack</i>

390
00:35:19,680 --> 00:35:22,040
<i>and I'm afraid my mission</i>
<i>to bring you to Alderaan has failed.</i>

391
00:35:22,120 --> 00:35:25,520
<i>I have placed information</i>
<i>vital to the survival of the rebellion</i>

392
00:35:25,600 --> 00:35:27,800
<i>into the memory systems</i>
<i>of this R2 unit.</i>

393
00:35:27,880 --> 00:35:29,440
<i>My father will know how to retrieve it.</i>

394
00:35:30,200 --> 00:35:33,960
<i>You must see this droid</i>
<i>safely delivered to him on Alderaan.</i>

395
00:35:34,040 --> 00:35:35,720
<i>This is our most desperate hour.</i>

396
00:35:36,480 --> 00:35:39,800
<i>Help me, Obi-Wan Kenobi.</i>
<i>You're my only hope.</i>

397
00:35:54,800 --> 00:35:58,920
You must learn the ways of the Force
if you're to come with me to Alderaan.

398
00:35:59,680 --> 00:36:01,040
Alderaan?

399
00:36:01,120 --> 00:36:02,360
I'm not going to Alderaan.

400
00:36:02,440 --> 00:36:04,840
I've gotta get home.
It's late. I'm in for it as it is.

401
00:36:04,920 --> 00:36:07,360
I need your help, Luke.
She needs your help.

402
00:36:07,880 --> 00:36:10,560
I'm getting too old for this sort of thing.

403
00:36:15,160 --> 00:36:18,520
I can't get involved. I've got work to do.

404
00:36:19,360 --> 00:36:21,200
It's not that I like the Empire. I hate it.

405
00:36:21,320 --> 00:36:23,840
But there's nothing
I can do about it right now.

406
00:36:25,360 --> 00:36:29,120
-It's all such a long way from here.
-That's your uncle talking.

407
00:36:29,200 --> 00:36:32,880
Oh, boy. My uncle.
How am I ever gonna explain this?

408
00:36:32,960 --> 00:36:34,680
Learn about the Force, Luke.

409
00:36:41,800 --> 00:36:44,560
I can take you as far as Anchorhead.

410
00:36:44,640 --> 00:36:48,000
You can get a transport there
to Mos Eisley or wherever you're going.

411
00:36:49,280 --> 00:36:52,280
You must do what you feel
is right, of course.

412
00:36:59,880 --> 00:37:03,520
Until this battle station is fully
operational, we are vulnerable.

413
00:37:03,600 --> 00:37:06,040
The Rebel Alliance
is too well equipped.

414
00:37:06,160 --> 00:37:07,800
They're more dangerous
than you realize.

415
00:37:07,880 --> 00:37:10,720
Dangerous to your starfleet,
Commander,

416
00:37:10,800 --> 00:37:12,600
not to this battle station.

417
00:37:12,680 --> 00:37:16,240
The rebellion will continue to
gain support in the Imperial Senate...

418
00:37:16,320 --> 00:37:20,680
The Imperial Senate will no longer
be of any concern to us.

419
00:37:20,800 --> 00:37:24,920
I've just received word that the emperor
has dissolved the council permanently.

420
00:37:25,000 --> 00:37:29,040
The last remnants of the old Republic
have been swept away.

421
00:37:29,120 --> 00:37:30,760
That's impossible.

422
00:37:30,840 --> 00:37:33,520
How will the emperor maintain control
without the bureaucracy?

423
00:37:33,600 --> 00:37:38,400
The regional governors now have
direct control over their territories.

424
00:37:38,480 --> 00:37:42,240
Fear will keep the local systems in line.

425
00:37:42,320 --> 00:37:44,440
Fear of this battle station.

426
00:37:44,520 --> 00:37:45,640
And what of the rebellion?

427
00:37:45,720 --> 00:37:48,920
If the rebels have obtained a complete
technical readout of this station,

428
00:37:49,000 --> 00:37:50,960
it is possible, however unlikely,

429
00:37:51,040 --> 00:37:53,200
that they might find a weakness
and exploit it.

430
00:37:53,760 --> 00:37:57,560
The plans you refer to
will soon be back in our hands.

431
00:37:57,640 --> 00:38:01,920
Any attack by the rebels against this
station would be a useless gesture,

432
00:38:02,000 --> 00:38:04,080
no matter what technical data
they've obtained.

433
00:38:04,160 --> 00:38:07,800
This station is now
the ultimate power in the universe.

434
00:38:08,440 --> 00:38:10,160
I suggest we use it.

435
00:38:10,240 --> 00:38:14,480
Don't be too proud of this
technological terror you've constructed.

436
00:38:14,560 --> 00:38:17,960
The ability to destroy a planet
is insignificant

437
00:38:18,040 --> 00:38:19,920
next to the power of the Force.

438
00:38:20,000 --> 00:38:23,480
Don't try to frighten us with
your sorcerer's ways, Lord Vader.

439
00:38:23,560 --> 00:38:26,440
Your sad devotion
to that ancient religion

440
00:38:26,520 --> 00:38:29,040
has not helped you conjure up
the stolen data tapes

441
00:38:29,600 --> 00:38:32,560
or given you clairvoyance enough
to find the rebels' hidden fortress...

442
00:38:40,200 --> 00:38:42,800
I find your lack of faith disturbing.

443
00:38:44,280 --> 00:38:46,920
Enough of this. Vader, release him.

444
00:38:47,000 --> 00:38:48,440
As you wish.

445
00:38:50,840 --> 00:38:52,800
This bickering is pointless.

446
00:38:53,920 --> 00:38:57,680
Lord Vader will provide us with
the location of the rebel fortress

447
00:38:57,760 --> 00:39:00,400
by the time this station is operational.

448
00:39:00,480 --> 00:39:04,520
We will then crush the rebellion
with one swift stroke.

449
00:39:11,440 --> 00:39:15,200
It looks like the Sandpeople did this.
There's gaffi sticks, Bantha tracks.

450
00:39:15,280 --> 00:39:17,600
I've just never heard of them
hitting anything this big before.

451
00:39:17,680 --> 00:39:21,040
They didn't, but we are
meant to think they did.

452
00:39:21,120 --> 00:39:23,040
These tracks are side-by-side.

453
00:39:23,120 --> 00:39:27,280
Sandpeople always ride single file
to hide their numbers.

454
00:39:27,360 --> 00:39:30,240
These are the same Jawas
that sold us R2 and 3PO.

455
00:39:30,320 --> 00:39:35,120
And these blast points,
too accurate for Sandpeople.

456
00:39:35,200 --> 00:39:39,120
Only imperial stormtroopers
are so precise.

457
00:39:39,200 --> 00:39:41,800
But why would imperial troops
want to slaughter Jawas?

458
00:39:47,160 --> 00:39:48,560
If they traced the robots here,

459
00:39:48,640 --> 00:39:49,920
they may have learned
who they sold them to

460
00:39:50,000 --> 00:39:52,440
and that would lead them back home.

461
00:39:52,520 --> 00:39:53,680
Wait, Luke.

462
00:39:53,760 --> 00:39:55,760
It's too dangerous.

463
00:40:19,800 --> 00:40:21,720
Uncle Owen.

464
00:40:21,800 --> 00:40:23,680
Aunt Beru.

465
00:40:23,760 --> 00:40:25,080
Uncle Owen.

466
00:41:15,360 --> 00:41:20,920
Now, Your Highness, we will discuss
the location of your hidden rebel base.

467
00:42:03,920 --> 00:42:06,240
There's nothing you could have done,
had you been there.

468
00:42:07,120 --> 00:42:09,080
You'd have been killed too,

469
00:42:09,160 --> 00:42:11,920
and the droids would now be
in the hands of the Empire.

470
00:42:13,600 --> 00:42:16,280
I want to come with you to Alderaan.

471
00:42:16,360 --> 00:42:18,400
There's nothing for me here now.

472
00:42:18,480 --> 00:42:21,440
I want to learn the ways of the Force
and become a Jedi like my father.

473
00:42:37,200 --> 00:42:39,600
Mos Eisley spaceport.

474
00:42:39,680 --> 00:42:45,280
You will never find a more wretched
hive of scum and villainy.

475
00:42:45,360 --> 00:42:46,840
We must be cautious.

476
00:43:28,200 --> 00:43:30,160
How long have you had these droids?

477
00:43:30,240 --> 00:43:33,360
-Three or four seasons.
-They're up for sale if you want them.

478
00:43:34,000 --> 00:43:35,400
Let me see your identification.

479
00:43:36,040 --> 00:43:39,040
You don't need to see his identification.

480
00:43:39,120 --> 00:43:41,240
We don't need to see his identification.

481
00:43:41,320 --> 00:43:44,160
These aren't the droids
you're looking for.

482
00:43:44,240 --> 00:43:45,920
These aren't the droids
we're looking for.

483
00:43:47,040 --> 00:43:49,440
He can go about his business.

484
00:43:49,520 --> 00:43:52,720
-You can go about your business.
-Move along.

485
00:43:53,040 --> 00:43:55,680
Move along. Move along.

486
00:44:11,720 --> 00:44:14,920
I can't abide those Jawas.
Disgusting creatures.

487
00:44:15,920 --> 00:44:17,840
Go on, go on.

488
00:44:19,200 --> 00:44:21,040
I can't understand
how we got by those troops.

489
00:44:21,120 --> 00:44:22,440
I thought we were dead.

490
00:44:22,520 --> 00:44:26,880
The Force can have a strong influence
on the weak-minded.

491
00:44:30,240 --> 00:44:33,480
You really think we're gonna find
a pilot here to take us to Alderaan?

492
00:44:33,560 --> 00:44:36,320
Most of the best freighter pilots
are to be found here.

493
00:44:36,440 --> 00:44:40,240
Only watch your step,
this place can be a little rough.

494
00:44:40,320 --> 00:44:42,000
I'm ready for anything.

495
00:44:45,800 --> 00:44:47,720
Come along, R2.

496
00:45:37,840 --> 00:45:41,400
-Hey. We don't serve their kind here.
-What?

497
00:45:41,480 --> 00:45:44,480
Your droids, they'll have to wait outside.
We don't want them here.

498
00:45:45,040 --> 00:45:46,960
Wait out by the speeder.
We don't want any trouble.

499
00:45:47,040 --> 00:45:49,000
I heartily agree with you, sir.

500
00:45:58,640 --> 00:46:00,120
I'll have one of those.

501
00:46:36,040 --> 00:46:38,920
-He doesn't like you.
-I'm sorry.

502
00:46:40,040 --> 00:46:43,680
I don't like you either.
You just watch yourself.

503
00:46:43,760 --> 00:46:48,360
We're wanted men. I have the
death sentence on 12 systems.

504
00:46:48,440 --> 00:46:51,240
-I'll be careful then.
-You'll be dead!

505
00:46:51,320 --> 00:46:53,280
This little one's not worth the effort.

506
00:46:54,440 --> 00:46:55,600
Come, let me get you something.

507
00:47:23,200 --> 00:47:24,960
I'm all right.

508
00:47:26,520 --> 00:47:31,120
Chewbacca here is first mate
on a ship that might suit us.

509
00:47:35,520 --> 00:47:37,560
I don't like the look of this.

510
00:47:52,360 --> 00:47:55,960
Han Solo. I'm captain
of the <i>Millennium Falcon.</i>

511
00:47:56,040 --> 00:47:59,280
Chewie here tells me you're looking
for passage to the Alderaan system.

512
00:47:59,360 --> 00:48:01,800
Yes, indeed, if it's a fast ship.

513
00:48:01,880 --> 00:48:06,120
Fast ship? You've never heard of
the <i>Millennium Falcon?</i>

514
00:48:06,240 --> 00:48:07,320
Should I have?

515
00:48:07,400 --> 00:48:10,560
It's the ship that made the Kessel run
in less than 12 parsecs.

516
00:48:12,600 --> 00:48:14,800
I've outrun imperial starships.

517
00:48:14,880 --> 00:48:16,880
Not the local bulk cruisers, mind you.

518
00:48:16,960 --> 00:48:19,160
I'm talking about
the big Corellian ships now.

519
00:48:21,000 --> 00:48:24,000
She's fast enough for you, old man.

520
00:48:24,080 --> 00:48:27,000
-What's the cargo?
-Only passengers.

521
00:48:27,080 --> 00:48:29,880
Myself, the boy, two droids...

522
00:48:31,000 --> 00:48:32,960
And no questions asked.

523
00:48:34,400 --> 00:48:36,120
Is it some kind of local trouble?

524
00:48:36,480 --> 00:48:41,320
Let's just say we'd like to avoid
any imperial entanglements.

525
00:48:42,760 --> 00:48:46,000
Well, that's the real trick, isn't it?

526
00:48:46,080 --> 00:48:47,680
And it's gonna cost you
something extra.

527
00:48:49,400 --> 00:48:51,200
Ten thousand, all in advance.

528
00:48:52,840 --> 00:48:54,200
Ten thousand?

529
00:48:55,520 --> 00:48:56,920
We could almost
buy our own ship for that.

530
00:48:58,200 --> 00:49:00,400
But who's gonna fly it, kid? You?

531
00:49:00,480 --> 00:49:02,560
You bet I could. I'm not such a bad pilot.

532
00:49:02,640 --> 00:49:05,160
We don't have to sit here and listen...

533
00:49:05,720 --> 00:49:08,040
We can pay you 2,000 now,

534
00:49:08,120 --> 00:49:11,360
plus 15 when we reach Alderaan.

535
00:49:12,320 --> 00:49:13,520
Seventeen?

536
00:49:17,000 --> 00:49:19,360
Okay, you guys got yourselves a ship.

537
00:49:19,440 --> 00:49:22,240
We'll leave as soon as you're ready.
Docking Bay 94.

538
00:49:22,320 --> 00:49:23,880
Ninety-four.

539
00:49:24,720 --> 00:49:28,840
Looks like somebody's beginning
to take an interest in your handiwork.

540
00:49:30,080 --> 00:49:31,920
All right. We'll check it out.

541
00:49:43,720 --> 00:49:47,360
Seventeen thousand. Those guys
must really be desperate.

542
00:49:47,440 --> 00:49:51,840
This could really save my neck.
Get back to the ship, get it ready.

543
00:49:51,920 --> 00:49:54,120
-You'll have to sell your speeder.
-That's okay.

544
00:49:54,200 --> 00:49:56,920
I'm never coming back
to this planet again.

545
00:49:57,520 --> 00:49:59,400
Going somewhere, Solo?

546
00:49:59,480 --> 00:50:02,760
Yes, Greedo. As a matter of fact,
I was just going to see your boss.

547
00:50:02,840 --> 00:50:05,040
Tell Jabba that I've got his money.

548
00:50:05,120 --> 00:50:06,840
It's too late.

549
00:50:06,920 --> 00:50:09,720
You should have paid him
when you had the chance.

550
00:50:09,800 --> 00:50:12,520
Jabba's put a price
on your head so large

551
00:50:12,600 --> 00:50:15,280
every bounty hunter in the galaxy
will be looking for you.

552
00:50:16,280 --> 00:50:18,240
I'm lucky I found you first.

553
00:50:18,320 --> 00:50:20,600
Yeah, but this time I've got the money.

554
00:50:20,680 --> 00:50:24,160
If you give it to me,
I might forget I found you.

555
00:50:24,680 --> 00:50:27,600
I don't have it with me. Tell Jabba...

556
00:50:27,680 --> 00:50:29,160
Jabba's through with you.

557
00:50:30,520 --> 00:50:32,840
He has no time for smugglers

558
00:50:32,920 --> 00:50:35,560
who drop their shipments
at the first sign of an Imperial cruiser.

559
00:50:35,680 --> 00:50:39,600
Even I get boarded sometimes.
Do you think I had a choice?

560
00:50:39,680 --> 00:50:43,680
You can tell that to Jabba.
He may only take your ship.

561
00:50:44,480 --> 00:50:45,920
Over my dead body.

562
00:50:46,000 --> 00:50:47,200
That's the idea.

563
00:50:47,280 --> 00:50:51,280
I've been looking forward
to this for a long time.

564
00:50:51,400 --> 00:50:52,680
I'll bet you have.

565
00:51:06,680 --> 00:51:08,760
Sorry about the mess.

566
00:51:17,680 --> 00:51:20,880
Her resistance to the mind probe
is considerable.

567
00:51:20,960 --> 00:51:24,280
It'll be some time before we can
extract any information from her.

568
00:51:24,360 --> 00:51:27,960
The final checkout is completed.
All systems are operational.

569
00:51:28,040 --> 00:51:30,280
What course shall we set?

570
00:51:30,400 --> 00:51:34,120
Perhaps she would respond
to an alternative form of persuasion.

571
00:51:34,200 --> 00:51:35,520
What do you mean?

572
00:51:35,600 --> 00:51:38,560
I think it is time we demonstrated
the full power of this station.

573
00:51:38,640 --> 00:51:41,120
-Set your course for Alderaan.
-With pleasure.

574
00:51:42,280 --> 00:51:44,320
Lock the door, R2.

575
00:51:46,400 --> 00:51:48,400
Check this side of the street.

576
00:51:52,560 --> 00:51:55,240
The door's locked.
Move on to the next one.

577
00:52:02,080 --> 00:52:04,760
I would much rather have gone with
Master Luke than stay here with you.

578
00:52:05,520 --> 00:52:09,080
I don't know what this trouble is about,
but I'm sure it must be your fault.

579
00:52:09,600 --> 00:52:11,240
You watch your language.

580
00:52:13,760 --> 00:52:16,680
All right. Give it to me. I'll take it.

581
00:52:16,760 --> 00:52:20,360
Look at this. Ever since the XP-38
came out, they just aren't in demand.

582
00:52:20,440 --> 00:52:22,440
It'll be enough.

583
00:52:40,800 --> 00:52:45,080
Solo! Come out of there, Solo!

584
00:52:45,160 --> 00:52:47,160
Right here, Jabba.

585
00:52:48,560 --> 00:52:49,960
I've been waitin' for you.

586
00:52:50,400 --> 00:52:53,000
Have you now.

587
00:52:53,880 --> 00:52:56,600
You didn't think I was gonna run,
did you?

588
00:52:56,680 --> 00:53:01,120
Han, my boy, you disappoint me.

589
00:53:01,200 --> 00:53:03,320
Why haven't you paid me

590
00:53:03,400 --> 00:53:06,800
and why did you fry poor Greedo?

591
00:53:06,880 --> 00:53:09,640
Jabba, next time you wanna talk to me,
come see me yourself.

592
00:53:09,720 --> 00:53:11,240
Don't send one of these twerps.

593
00:53:11,320 --> 00:53:14,800
Han, I can't make exceptions.

594
00:53:14,880 --> 00:53:17,760
What if everyone who smuggled for me

595
00:53:17,880 --> 00:53:20,480
dropped their cargo at the first sign

596
00:53:20,560 --> 00:53:23,240
of an imperial starship?

597
00:53:23,320 --> 00:53:25,400
It's not good business.

598
00:53:25,480 --> 00:53:28,920
Look, Jabba,
even I get boarded sometimes.

599
00:53:29,760 --> 00:53:32,280
You think I had a choice?

600
00:53:32,360 --> 00:53:34,280
But I got a nice, easy charter.

601
00:53:34,400 --> 00:53:38,440
I'll pay ya back, plus a little extra.
I just need a little more time.

602
00:53:38,520 --> 00:53:44,080
Han, my boy, you're the best.

603
00:53:44,160 --> 00:53:46,600
So, for an extra twenty percent...

604
00:53:46,680 --> 00:53:48,840
Fifteen, Jabba. Don't push it.

605
00:53:48,920 --> 00:53:50,840
Okay, fifteen percent.

606
00:53:50,920 --> 00:53:53,120
But if you fail me again,

607
00:53:53,200 --> 00:53:56,120
I'll put a price on your head so big

608
00:53:56,200 --> 00:54:00,440
you won't be able to
go near a civilized system.

609
00:54:00,520 --> 00:54:03,280
Jabba, you're a
wonderful human being.

610
00:54:04,760 --> 00:54:05,920
Come on!

611
00:54:12,200 --> 00:54:15,880
If the ship's as fast as he's boasting,
we ought to do well.

612
00:54:39,560 --> 00:54:41,240
What a piece of junk.

613
00:54:41,320 --> 00:54:43,840
She'll make .5 past light speed.

614
00:54:43,920 --> 00:54:46,720
She may not look like much,
but she's got it where it counts, kid.

615
00:54:46,800 --> 00:54:49,760
I've made a lot of special
modifications myself.

616
00:54:49,840 --> 00:54:53,760
But we're a little rushed, so if you'll
just get on board, we'll get outta here.

617
00:54:58,920 --> 00:55:00,440
Hello, sir.

618
00:55:08,920 --> 00:55:10,160
Which way?

619
00:55:12,000 --> 00:55:14,000
All right, men, load your weapons.

620
00:55:16,280 --> 00:55:18,240
Stop that ship. Blast them.

621
00:55:28,040 --> 00:55:30,040
Chewie, get us out of here!

622
00:55:31,440 --> 00:55:35,040
Oh, my. I'd forgotten
how much I hate space travel.

623
00:55:54,000 --> 00:55:55,280
Looks like an imperial cruiser.

624
00:55:55,360 --> 00:55:57,080
Our passengers
are hotter than I thought.

625
00:55:57,160 --> 00:55:58,760
Hold 'em off. Angle the deflector shields

626
00:55:58,840 --> 00:56:00,760
while I make the calculations
for the jump to light speed.

627
00:56:11,520 --> 00:56:14,400
Stay sharp. There's two more comin' in.
They're gonna try and cut us off.

628
00:56:14,480 --> 00:56:16,600
Why don't you outrun 'em?
You said this thing was fast.

629
00:56:16,680 --> 00:56:18,600
Watch your mouth or you're gonna
find yourself floating home.

630
00:56:19,200 --> 00:56:22,040
We'll be safe enough
once we make the jump to hyperspace.

631
00:56:22,120 --> 00:56:24,000
Besides, I know a few maneuvers.
We'll lose 'em.

632
00:56:28,960 --> 00:56:30,160
Here's where the fun begins.

633
00:56:30,280 --> 00:56:32,040
How long before you can
jump to light speed?

634
00:56:32,680 --> 00:56:35,040
It'll take a few moments to get
the coordinates from the navicomputer.

635
00:56:35,120 --> 00:56:36,720
Are you kidding?
At the rate they're gaining?

636
00:56:37,240 --> 00:56:39,800
Traveling through hyperspace
ain't like dustin' crops, boy.

637
00:56:39,920 --> 00:56:42,400
Without precise calculations,
we'd fly right through a star

638
00:56:42,480 --> 00:56:46,400
or bounce too close to a supernova,
and that would end your trip real quick.

639
00:56:46,480 --> 00:56:48,640
-What's that flashing?
-We're losing a deflector shield.

640
00:56:48,720 --> 00:56:51,680
Go strap yourselves in.
I'm gonna make the jump to light speed.

641
00:57:13,120 --> 00:57:15,800
We've entered the Alderaan system.

642
00:57:15,880 --> 00:57:17,240
Governor Tarkin.

643
00:57:17,320 --> 00:57:19,920
I should have expected
to find you holding Vader's leash.

644
00:57:20,280 --> 00:57:23,640
I recognized your foul stench
when I was brought on board.

645
00:57:25,240 --> 00:57:27,120
Charming to the last.

646
00:57:27,960 --> 00:57:29,760
You don't know how hard I found it

647
00:57:29,880 --> 00:57:31,760
signing the order to terminate your life.

648
00:57:31,840 --> 00:57:34,800
I'm surprised you had the courage
to take the responsibility yourself.

649
00:57:35,160 --> 00:57:37,960
Princess Leia, before your execution,

650
00:57:38,040 --> 00:57:40,480
I would like you to be my guest
at a ceremony

651
00:57:40,560 --> 00:57:43,520
that will make
this battle station operational.

652
00:57:43,600 --> 00:57:46,840
No star system will dare
oppose the emperor now.

653
00:57:46,920 --> 00:57:49,200
The more you tighten your grip, Tarkin,

654
00:57:49,280 --> 00:57:51,880
the more star systems
will slip through your fingers.

655
00:57:51,960 --> 00:57:55,280
Not after we demonstrate
the power of this station.

656
00:57:55,360 --> 00:57:58,800
In a way, you have determined
the choice of the planet

657
00:57:58,880 --> 00:58:01,040
that'll be destroyed first.

658
00:58:01,120 --> 00:58:05,640
Since you are reluctant to provide us
with the location of the rebel base,

659
00:58:05,720 --> 00:58:08,520
I have chosen to test
this station's destructive power

660
00:58:08,600 --> 00:58:11,600
on your home planet of Alderaan.

661
00:58:11,680 --> 00:58:14,360
No. Alderaan is peaceful.
We have no weapons.

662
00:58:14,440 --> 00:58:16,880
You would prefer another target?
A military target?

663
00:58:16,960 --> 00:58:19,120
Then name the system.

664
00:58:21,080 --> 00:58:24,480
I grow tired of asking this,
so it will be the last time.

665
00:58:25,200 --> 00:58:27,160
Where is the rebel base?

666
00:58:31,280 --> 00:58:32,840
Dantooine.

667
00:58:33,720 --> 00:58:34,840
They're on Dantooine.

668
00:58:34,920 --> 00:58:38,360
There. You see, Lord Vader?
She can be reasonable.

669
00:58:38,440 --> 00:58:41,200
Continue with the operation.
You may fire when ready.

670
00:58:41,280 --> 00:58:43,520
-What?
-You're far too trusting.

671
00:58:43,840 --> 00:58:46,440
Dantooine is too remote
to make an effective demonstration.

672
00:58:46,520 --> 00:58:50,560
But don't worry. We will deal with
your rebel friends soon enough.

673
00:58:53,840 --> 00:58:55,200
Commence primary ignition.

674
00:59:18,520 --> 00:59:21,040
Are you all right? What's wrong?

675
00:59:22,080 --> 00:59:24,560
I felt a great disturbance in the Force

676
00:59:24,640 --> 00:59:27,720
as if millions of voices suddenly
cried out in terror

677
00:59:27,800 --> 00:59:30,200
and were suddenly silenced.

678
00:59:30,280 --> 00:59:32,360
I fear something terrible has happened.

679
00:59:34,040 --> 00:59:36,280
You'd better get on with your exercises.

680
00:59:39,080 --> 00:59:41,680
You can forget your troubles
with those imperial slugs.

681
00:59:41,760 --> 00:59:44,160
I told you I'd outrun them.

682
00:59:47,720 --> 00:59:49,440
Don't everybody thank me at once.

683
00:59:50,240 --> 00:59:53,680
Anyway, we should be at Alderaan
about 0200 hours.

684
01:00:01,480 --> 01:00:03,480
Now be careful, R2.

685
01:00:12,800 --> 01:00:15,440
He made a fair move.
Screaming about it can't help you.

686
01:00:15,520 --> 01:00:17,800
Let him have it.
It's not wise to upset a Wookiee.

687
01:00:17,880 --> 01:00:20,160
But, sir, nobody worries
about upsetting a droid.

688
01:00:20,520 --> 01:00:22,760
That's 'cause a droid
don't pull people's arms

689
01:00:22,840 --> 01:00:24,840
out of their sockets when they lose.

690
01:00:25,280 --> 01:00:27,520
Wookiees are known to do that.

691
01:00:29,440 --> 01:00:31,080
I see your point, sir.

692
01:00:31,160 --> 01:00:34,400
I suggest a new strategy, R2.
Let the Wookiee win.

693
01:00:52,880 --> 01:00:56,520
Remember, a Jedi can feel the Force
flowing through him.

694
01:00:57,280 --> 01:00:59,600
-You mean it controls your actions?
-Partially.

695
01:00:59,680 --> 01:01:01,600
But it also obeys your commands.

696
01:01:07,080 --> 01:01:08,840
Hokey religions and ancient weapons

697
01:01:08,920 --> 01:01:11,120
are no match
for a blaster at your side, kid.

698
01:01:12,040 --> 01:01:13,520
You don't believe in the Force, do you?

699
01:01:14,560 --> 01:01:17,040
Kid, I've flown from one side
of this galaxy to the other.

700
01:01:17,120 --> 01:01:18,720
I've seen a lot of strange stuff,

701
01:01:18,800 --> 01:01:21,040
but I've never seen anything
to make me believe

702
01:01:21,120 --> 01:01:24,560
there's one all-powerful force
controlling everything.

703
01:01:25,120 --> 01:01:28,800
There's no mystical energy field
controls my destiny.

704
01:01:28,880 --> 01:01:31,840
It's all a lot of
simple tricks and nonsense.

705
01:01:31,920 --> 01:01:34,800
I suggest you try it again, Luke.

706
01:01:36,360 --> 01:01:39,040
This time, let go your conscious self

707
01:01:41,080 --> 01:01:43,320
and act on instinct.

708
01:01:44,320 --> 01:01:47,840
With the blast shield down, I can't see.
How am I supposed to fight?

709
01:01:47,920 --> 01:01:50,080
Your eyes can deceive you.
Don't trust them.

710
01:01:59,920 --> 01:02:01,880
Stretch out with your feelings.

711
01:02:16,520 --> 01:02:18,480
You see? You can do it.

712
01:02:19,120 --> 01:02:20,280
I call it luck.

713
01:02:20,360 --> 01:02:22,960
In my experience,
there's no such thing as luck.

714
01:02:23,480 --> 01:02:25,600
Good against remotes is one thing.

715
01:02:25,720 --> 01:02:28,880
Good against the living,
that's something else.

716
01:02:29,880 --> 01:02:31,520
We're coming up on Alderaan.

717
01:02:35,000 --> 01:02:37,800
I did feel something.
I could almost see the remote.

718
01:02:37,880 --> 01:02:42,640
That's good. You've taken
your first step into a larger world.

719
01:02:47,320 --> 01:02:49,120
Yes?

720
01:02:49,200 --> 01:02:50,920
Our scout ships
have reached Dantooine.

721
01:02:51,040 --> 01:02:52,880
They found the remains of a rebel base,

722
01:02:52,960 --> 01:02:55,400
but they estimate that
it has been deserted for some time.

723
01:02:55,480 --> 01:02:59,160
They are now conducting an extensive
search of the surrounding systems.

724
01:02:59,840 --> 01:03:02,400
She lied. She lied to us.

725
01:03:02,480 --> 01:03:06,160
I told you she would never
consciously betray the rebellion.

726
01:03:07,680 --> 01:03:09,840
Terminate her immediately.

727
01:03:12,680 --> 01:03:15,200
Stand by, Chewie. Here we go.
Cut in the sublight engines.

728
01:03:18,000 --> 01:03:19,160
What the...

729
01:03:22,760 --> 01:03:24,520
We've come out of hyperspace
into a meteor shower,

730
01:03:24,600 --> 01:03:26,000
some kind of asteroid collision.

731
01:03:26,360 --> 01:03:28,480
-It's not on any of the charts.
-What's going on?

732
01:03:28,560 --> 01:03:30,840
Our position's correct,
except no Alderaan.

733
01:03:31,280 --> 01:03:33,360
-Where is it?
-That's what I'm trying to tell you.

734
01:03:33,440 --> 01:03:35,160
It ain't there. It's been blown away.

735
01:03:35,240 --> 01:03:37,920
-What? How?
-Destroyed by the Empire.

736
01:03:38,040 --> 01:03:40,200
The entire starfleet
couldn't destroy the whole planet.

737
01:03:40,280 --> 01:03:43,240
It'd take a thousand ships
with more firepower than I've...

738
01:03:44,360 --> 01:03:46,720
-There's another ship coming in.
-Maybe they know what happened.

739
01:03:46,800 --> 01:03:48,120
It's an imperial fighter.

740
01:03:50,160 --> 01:03:53,080
-It followed us.
-No. It's a short-range fighter.

741
01:03:53,160 --> 01:03:54,960
There aren't any bases around here.
Where did it come from?

742
01:03:58,200 --> 01:04:00,960
Sure is leaving in a hurry.
If they identify us, we're in trouble.

743
01:04:01,040 --> 01:04:03,200
Not if I can help it.
Chewie, jam its transmissions.

744
01:04:03,280 --> 01:04:06,720
-Let it go. It's too far out of range.
-Not for long.

745
01:04:10,480 --> 01:04:13,800
A fighter that size couldn't get
this deep into space on its own.

746
01:04:13,880 --> 01:04:16,760
He must have gotten lost,
been part of a convoy or something.

747
01:04:16,840 --> 01:04:19,400
He ain't gonna be around
long enough to tell anybody about us.

748
01:04:22,040 --> 01:04:23,880
He's heading for that small moon.

749
01:04:23,960 --> 01:04:26,520
I can get him before he gets there.
He's almost in range.

750
01:04:28,080 --> 01:04:30,160
That's no moon.

751
01:04:30,240 --> 01:04:33,600
-It's a space station.
-It's too big to be a space station.

752
01:04:36,960 --> 01:04:39,440
I have a very bad feeling about this.

753
01:04:39,520 --> 01:04:41,360
Turn the ship around.

754
01:04:41,440 --> 01:04:44,000
Yeah. I think you're right. Full reverse.

755
01:04:44,080 --> 01:04:45,760
Chewie, lock in the auxiliary power.

756
01:04:50,600 --> 01:04:52,760
Chewie, lock in the auxiliary power.

757
01:04:55,120 --> 01:04:56,680
Why are we still moving towards it?

758
01:04:56,760 --> 01:04:58,600
We're caught in a tractor beam.
It's pulling us in.

759
01:04:58,680 --> 01:05:00,240
There's gotta be something you can do.

760
01:05:00,320 --> 01:05:03,200
There's nothing I can do.
I'm at full power. I have to shut down.

761
01:05:03,280 --> 01:05:04,800
They're not gonna
get me without a fight.

762
01:05:09,440 --> 01:05:12,880
You can't win,
but there are alternatives to fighting.

763
01:05:29,520 --> 01:05:31,640
<i>Clear Bay 327.</i>

764
01:05:31,720 --> 01:05:34,080
<i>We are opening the magnetic field.</i>

765
01:05:48,720 --> 01:05:51,040
To your stations. Come with me.

766
01:05:55,480 --> 01:05:59,120
<i>Close all outboard shields.</i>
<i>Close all outboard shields.</i>

767
01:06:00,480 --> 01:06:01,520
Yes?

768
01:06:01,600 --> 01:06:04,600
<i>We've captured a freighter entering</i>
<i>the remains of the Alderaan system.</i>

769
01:06:04,680 --> 01:06:08,640
<i>Its markings match those of a ship</i>
<i>that blasted its way out of Mos Eisley.</i>

770
01:06:08,720 --> 01:06:12,440
They must be trying to return
the stolen plans to the princess.

771
01:06:12,520 --> 01:06:15,520
She may yet be of some use to us.

772
01:06:20,440 --> 01:06:24,400
<i>Unlock one, five, seven and nine.</i>
<i>Release charge.</i>

773
01:06:31,920 --> 01:06:33,080
There's no one on board, sir.

774
01:06:33,160 --> 01:06:35,920
According to the log, the crew
abandoned ship right after takeoff.

775
01:06:36,640 --> 01:06:39,680
It must be a decoy. Several escape
pods have been jettisoned.

776
01:06:39,760 --> 01:06:41,640
-Did you find any droids?
-No, sir.

777
01:06:41,720 --> 01:06:43,600
If there were any,
they must also have jettisoned.

778
01:06:43,680 --> 01:06:47,200
Send a scanning crew aboard.
I want every part of this ship checked.

779
01:06:47,280 --> 01:06:48,440
Yes, sir.

780
01:06:48,520 --> 01:06:50,080
I sense something,

781
01:06:50,160 --> 01:06:53,000
a presence I've not felt since...

782
01:06:55,400 --> 01:06:58,800
Get me a scanning crew in here.
I want every part of this ship checked.

783
01:07:07,560 --> 01:07:09,560
There's no one here.

784
01:07:18,800 --> 01:07:20,800
Boy, it's lucky you have
these compartments.

785
01:07:20,880 --> 01:07:23,960
I use them for smuggling. I never
thought I'd be smuggling myself in 'em.

786
01:07:24,040 --> 01:07:25,240
This is ridiculous.

787
01:07:25,320 --> 01:07:28,080
Even if I could take off,
I'd never get past the tractor beam.

788
01:07:28,160 --> 01:07:29,280
Leave that to me.

789
01:07:29,360 --> 01:07:32,600
Damn fool.
I knew you were gonna say that.

790
01:07:32,680 --> 01:07:36,320
Who's the more foolish,
the fool or the fool who follows him?

791
01:07:45,600 --> 01:07:50,160
The ship's all yours. If the scanners
pick up anything, report it immediately.

792
01:07:51,040 --> 01:07:53,000
All right. Let's go.

793
01:08:07,240 --> 01:08:09,240
Hey, down there.

794
01:08:11,000 --> 01:08:13,000
Could you give us a hand with this?

795
01:08:21,400 --> 01:08:24,640
TK-421, why aren't you at your post?

796
01:08:24,720 --> 01:08:26,720
TK-421, do you copy?

797
01:08:39,160 --> 01:08:42,360
Take over. We've got a bad transmitter.
I'll see what I can do.

798
01:08:59,720 --> 01:09:01,720
Between his howling
and your blasting everything,

799
01:09:01,800 --> 01:09:04,080
it's a wonder the whole station
doesn't know we're here.

800
01:09:04,160 --> 01:09:07,480
Bring 'em on. I prefer a straight fight
to sneakin' around.

801
01:09:07,560 --> 01:09:09,320
We've found the computer outlet, sir.

802
01:09:09,400 --> 01:09:12,440
Plug in. He should be able to
interpret the entire imperial network.

803
01:09:23,840 --> 01:09:27,200
He's found the controls to the power
beam that's holding the ship here.

804
01:09:27,280 --> 01:09:29,880
He'll try to make the precise location
appear on the monitor.

805
01:09:30,560 --> 01:09:34,480
The tractor beam is coupled
to the main reactor in seven locations.

806
01:09:34,560 --> 01:09:37,880
A power loss at one of the terminals
will allow the ship to leave.

807
01:09:40,320 --> 01:09:43,560
I don't think you boys can help.
I must go alone.

808
01:09:43,640 --> 01:09:47,160
Whatever you say. I've done more than
I bargained for on this trip already.

809
01:09:47,240 --> 01:09:51,280
-I want to go with you.
-Be patient, Luke. Watch the droids.

810
01:09:51,360 --> 01:09:52,760
They must be delivered safely

811
01:09:52,880 --> 01:09:56,560
or other star systems will suffer
the same fate as Alderaan.

812
01:09:56,640 --> 01:09:59,960
Your destiny lies along
a different path from mine.

813
01:10:03,600 --> 01:10:05,400
The Force will be with you...

814
01:10:05,800 --> 01:10:07,200
Always.

815
01:10:16,320 --> 01:10:18,640
You said it, Chewie.

816
01:10:18,720 --> 01:10:21,120
Where did you dig up that old fossil?

817
01:10:22,400 --> 01:10:23,880
Ben is a great man.

818
01:10:23,960 --> 01:10:27,040
-Great at getting us into trouble.
-I didn't hear you give any ideas.

819
01:10:27,160 --> 01:10:30,000
Anything's better than just hangin'
around waiting for 'em to pick us up.

820
01:10:30,080 --> 01:10:31,600
Who do you think...

821
01:10:32,440 --> 01:10:35,680
-What is it?
-I'm afraid I'm not quite sure, sir.

822
01:10:35,760 --> 01:10:38,640
He says, "I've found her,"
and keeps repeating, "She's here."

823
01:10:38,720 --> 01:10:41,240
Who? Who has he found?

824
01:10:41,320 --> 01:10:43,960
-Princess Leia.
-The princess? She's here?

825
01:10:44,040 --> 01:10:45,720
-Princess?
-Where is she?

826
01:10:45,800 --> 01:10:47,720
Princess? What's going on?

827
01:10:53,120 --> 01:10:55,920
Level 5, Detention Block AA-23.

828
01:11:00,720 --> 01:11:03,400
I'm afraid she's scheduled
to be terminated.

829
01:11:03,480 --> 01:11:06,480
Oh, no. We've gotta do something.

830
01:11:06,560 --> 01:11:09,040
-What are you talking about?
-The droids belong to her.

831
01:11:09,160 --> 01:11:11,040
She's the one in the message.
We gotta help her.

832
01:11:11,160 --> 01:11:14,040
Don't get any funny ideas.
The old man wants us to wait here.

833
01:11:14,120 --> 01:11:17,400
He didn't know she was here.
Find a way into that detention block.

834
01:11:17,480 --> 01:11:20,360
-I'm not going anywhere.
-They're gonna execute her.

835
01:11:20,440 --> 01:11:23,840
You said you didn't want to just wait
to be captured. Now you want to stay?

836
01:11:23,920 --> 01:11:26,760
Marching into the detention area
is not what I had in mind.

837
01:11:26,840 --> 01:11:29,680
-But they're gonna kill her.
-Better her than me.

838
01:11:37,600 --> 01:11:38,760
She's rich.

839
01:11:41,920 --> 01:11:43,400
Rich?

840
01:11:43,480 --> 01:11:47,760
Rich, powerful. If you were to
rescue her, the reward would be...

841
01:11:47,840 --> 01:11:50,400
-What?
-Well, more well than you can imagine.

842
01:11:50,480 --> 01:11:52,600
I don't know. I can imagine quite a bit.

843
01:11:52,680 --> 01:11:54,600
-You'll get it.
-I better.

844
01:11:54,680 --> 01:11:56,440
You will.

845
01:11:56,520 --> 01:11:58,760
All right, kid.
You better be right about this.

846
01:11:58,880 --> 01:12:00,800
-All right.
-What's your plan?

847
01:12:01,840 --> 01:12:04,320
3PO, hand me those binders there,
will you?

848
01:12:05,880 --> 01:12:07,280
Okay.

849
01:12:07,960 --> 01:12:09,960
Now, I'm gonna put these on you.

850
01:12:11,360 --> 01:12:14,600
Okay, Han, you put those on.

851
01:12:15,400 --> 01:12:17,800
Don't worry, Chewie.
I think I know what he has in mind.

852
01:12:18,840 --> 01:12:20,680
Master Luke, sir, pardon me for asking,

853
01:12:20,760 --> 01:12:23,600
but what should R2 and I do
if we're discovered here?

854
01:12:24,360 --> 01:12:27,640
-Lock the door.
-And hope they don't have blasters.

855
01:12:27,720 --> 01:12:29,720
That isn't very reassuring.

856
01:12:50,000 --> 01:12:54,640
<i>517 to scan control.</i>
<i>517 to scan control.</i>

857
01:13:21,200 --> 01:13:23,520
I can't see a thing in this helmet.

858
01:13:54,760 --> 01:13:57,520
-This is not gonna work.
-Why didn't you say so before?

859
01:13:57,600 --> 01:13:59,560
I did say so before.

860
01:14:14,520 --> 01:14:17,800
Where are you taking this thing?

861
01:14:17,880 --> 01:14:20,640
Prisoner transfer from Cell Block 1138.

862
01:14:21,920 --> 01:14:23,880
I wasn't notified.

863
01:14:23,960 --> 01:14:25,920
I'll have to clear it.

864
01:14:32,440 --> 01:14:34,960
-Look out! He's loose!
-He'll tear us all apart!

865
01:14:59,280 --> 01:15:00,280
Look out.

866
01:15:10,480 --> 01:15:12,960
We gotta find out which cell
this princess of yours is in.

867
01:15:13,040 --> 01:15:15,280
Here it is. 2187. You go and get her.

868
01:15:15,360 --> 01:15:17,320
I'll hold them here.

869
01:15:21,640 --> 01:15:23,840
Everything's under control.
Situation normal.

870
01:15:23,920 --> 01:15:25,040
<i>What happened?</i>

871
01:15:25,120 --> 01:15:27,160
Had a slight weapons malfunction,

872
01:15:27,240 --> 01:15:29,640
but everything's perfectly all right now.

873
01:15:29,720 --> 01:15:32,960
We're fine. We're all fine here now.
Thank you.

874
01:15:33,040 --> 01:15:35,680
-How are you?
<i>-We're sending a squad up.</i>

875
01:15:36,640 --> 01:15:40,040
Negative, negative.
We have a reactor leak here now.

876
01:15:40,120 --> 01:15:43,880
Give us a few minutes to lock it down.
Large leak, very dangerous.

877
01:15:43,960 --> 01:15:47,040
<i>Who is this?</i>
<i>What's your operating number?</i>

878
01:15:48,920 --> 01:15:52,640
Boring conversation anyway.
Luke, we're gonna have company!

879
01:16:06,680 --> 01:16:08,640
Aren't you a little short
for a stormtrooper?

880
01:16:09,760 --> 01:16:11,280
Oh, the uniform.

881
01:16:13,160 --> 01:16:15,160
I'm Luke Skywalker.
I'm here to rescue you.

882
01:16:15,240 --> 01:16:16,240
You're who?

883
01:16:16,320 --> 01:16:18,080
I'm here to rescue you.
I've got your R2 unit.

884
01:16:18,160 --> 01:16:20,160
-I'm here with Ben Kenobi.
-Ben Kenobi? Where is he?

885
01:16:20,240 --> 01:16:21,480
Come on.

886
01:16:23,280 --> 01:16:27,160
-He is here.
-Obi-Wan Kenobi?

887
01:16:27,240 --> 01:16:30,600
-What makes you think so?
-A tremor in the Force.

888
01:16:30,680 --> 01:16:34,680
The last time I felt it
was in the presence of my old master.

889
01:16:34,760 --> 01:16:37,080
Surely he must be dead by now.

890
01:16:37,200 --> 01:16:39,960
Don't underestimate the Force.

891
01:16:40,600 --> 01:16:44,680
The Jedi are extinct.
Their fire has gone out of the universe.

892
01:16:44,760 --> 01:16:48,080
You, my friend, are all that's left
of their religion.

893
01:16:48,160 --> 01:16:49,360
Yes.

894
01:16:49,440 --> 01:16:52,960
<i>We have an emergency alert</i>
<i>in Detention Block AA-23.</i>

895
01:16:53,680 --> 01:16:56,360
The princess? Put all sections on alert.

896
01:16:56,440 --> 01:16:59,960
Obi-Wan is here. The Force is with him.

897
01:17:00,040 --> 01:17:02,880
If you're right,
he must not be allowed to escape.

898
01:17:02,960 --> 01:17:06,480
Escape is not his plan.
I must face him alone.

899
01:17:15,960 --> 01:17:17,560
Get behind me. Get behind me.

900
01:17:29,120 --> 01:17:31,440
Watch your left.
They went down the cell bay.

901
01:17:34,480 --> 01:17:37,400
-Can't get out that way.
-You cut off our only escape route.

902
01:17:37,480 --> 01:17:40,480
Maybe you'd like it back in your cell,
Your Highness.

903
01:17:42,520 --> 01:17:44,760
-C-3PO. C-3PO.
<i>-Yes, sir?</i>

904
01:17:44,840 --> 01:17:48,320
Are there any other ways out of
the cell bay? We've been cut off.

905
01:17:50,760 --> 01:17:52,840
What was that? I didn't copy.

906
01:17:52,920 --> 01:17:56,320
I said all systems have been
alerted to your presence, sir.

907
01:17:56,400 --> 01:17:58,920
The main entrance
seems to be the only way in or out.

908
01:17:59,000 --> 01:18:01,280
All other information on your level
is restricted.

909
01:18:01,360 --> 01:18:04,360
Open up in there. Open up in there.

910
01:18:05,200 --> 01:18:06,640
Oh, no.

911
01:18:06,720 --> 01:18:08,360
There isn't any other way out.

912
01:18:13,840 --> 01:18:16,200
I can't hold them off forever. Now what?

913
01:18:16,280 --> 01:18:17,320
This is some rescue.

914
01:18:17,680 --> 01:18:19,760
When you came in here,
didn't you have a plan for getting out?

915
01:18:19,880 --> 01:18:21,880
He's the brains, sweetheart.

916
01:18:21,960 --> 01:18:23,560
Well, I didn't...

917
01:18:25,000 --> 01:18:28,200
-What the hell are you doing?
-Somebody has to save our skins.

918
01:18:30,400 --> 01:18:32,200
Into the garbage chute, flyboy.

919
01:18:39,760 --> 01:18:40,800
Get in there!

920
01:18:41,960 --> 01:18:44,960
Get in there, you big furry oaf.
I don't care what you smell.

921
01:18:46,040 --> 01:18:48,320
Get in there, and don't worry about it.

922
01:18:51,040 --> 01:18:52,080
Wonderful girl.

923
01:18:54,240 --> 01:18:56,240
Either I'm gonna kill her,
or I'm beginning to like her.

924
01:18:58,920 --> 01:18:59,920
Get in there.

925
01:19:13,520 --> 01:19:17,000
The garbage chute was
a really wonderful idea.

926
01:19:17,080 --> 01:19:19,520
What an incredible smell
you've discovered.

927
01:19:22,560 --> 01:19:24,400
Let's get out of here.

928
01:19:24,480 --> 01:19:26,920
-Get away from there.
-No, wait.

929
01:19:33,560 --> 01:19:35,920
Forget it! I already tried it!
It's magnetically sealed.

930
01:19:36,040 --> 01:19:38,360
Put that thing away!
You're gonna get us all killed!

931
01:19:38,440 --> 01:19:40,160
Absolutely, Your Worship.

932
01:19:40,240 --> 01:19:42,680
Look, I had everything under control
till you led us down here.

933
01:19:43,400 --> 01:19:45,800
It's not gonna take 'em long
to figure out what happened to us.

934
01:19:45,880 --> 01:19:47,160
It could be worse.

935
01:19:52,000 --> 01:19:53,080
It's worse.

936
01:19:53,160 --> 01:19:56,160
-There's something alive in here.
-That's your imagination.

937
01:19:57,120 --> 01:19:58,920
Something just moved past my leg.

938
01:20:00,800 --> 01:20:03,800
-Look. Did you see that?
-What?

939
01:20:25,480 --> 01:20:27,200
Kid! Luke!

940
01:20:39,800 --> 01:20:41,560
Grab hold of this!

941
01:20:41,880 --> 01:20:44,000
Blast it! My gun's jammed.

942
01:20:44,080 --> 01:20:46,840
-Where?
-Anywhere!

943
01:21:19,440 --> 01:21:21,080
Help him!

944
01:21:21,160 --> 01:21:23,160
-What happened?
-I don't know.

945
01:21:23,240 --> 01:21:26,080
It just let go of me and disappeared.

946
01:21:32,080 --> 01:21:34,520
I got a bad feeling about this.

947
01:21:40,240 --> 01:21:43,400
-The walls are moving!
-Try and brace it with something.

948
01:21:52,080 --> 01:21:53,600
Help me.

949
01:22:06,520 --> 01:22:08,320
Wait a minute.

950
01:22:10,680 --> 01:22:13,880
3PO! Come in, 3PO!

951
01:22:14,680 --> 01:22:16,160
<i>3PO!</i>

952
01:22:16,240 --> 01:22:18,320
<i>Where could he be?</i>

953
01:22:22,480 --> 01:22:24,640
Take over. See to him.

954
01:22:27,120 --> 01:22:28,600
Look, there.

955
01:22:31,040 --> 01:22:33,400
They're madmen.
They're heading for the prison level.

956
01:22:33,480 --> 01:22:35,400
If you hurry, you might catch them.

957
01:22:35,480 --> 01:22:37,000
Follow me.

958
01:22:40,720 --> 01:22:42,760
You stand guard.

959
01:22:47,480 --> 01:22:48,800
Come on.

960
01:22:56,720 --> 01:22:59,880
All this excitement has overrun
the circuits in my counterpart here.

961
01:23:00,000 --> 01:23:03,120
If you don't mind, I'd like to
take him down to maintenance.

962
01:23:03,200 --> 01:23:04,720
All right.

963
01:23:16,920 --> 01:23:19,720
3PO. Come in, 3PO.

964
01:23:19,800 --> 01:23:21,200
3PO.

965
01:23:21,280 --> 01:23:24,000
-Get on top.
-I can't.

966
01:23:24,080 --> 01:23:25,960
Where could he be? 3PO.

967
01:23:27,360 --> 01:23:29,200
3PO, will you come in?

968
01:23:29,920 --> 01:23:32,240
They aren't here. Something must have
happened to them.

969
01:23:32,320 --> 01:23:34,880
See if they've been captured. Hurry.

970
01:23:38,720 --> 01:23:41,640
One thing's for sure.
We're all gonna be a lot thinner.

971
01:23:44,080 --> 01:23:46,880
-Get on top of it.
-I'm trying.

972
01:23:52,240 --> 01:23:56,160
Thank goodness they haven't
found them. Where could they be?

973
01:23:57,560 --> 01:24:00,280
"Use the comlink"? Oh, my.

974
01:24:00,360 --> 01:24:01,920
I forgot. I turned it off.

975
01:24:06,160 --> 01:24:08,920
-Are you there, sir?
-3PO?

976
01:24:09,240 --> 01:24:11,920
-We've had some problems.
<i>-Shut up and listen to me.</i>

977
01:24:12,000 --> 01:24:15,760
<i>Shut down all the garbage mashers</i>
<i>on the detention level. Do you copy?</i>

978
01:24:15,840 --> 01:24:18,800
Shut down all the garbage mashers
on the detention level!

979
01:24:19,920 --> 01:24:22,600
<i>Shut down all the garbage mashers</i>
<i>on the detention level!</i>

980
01:24:22,680 --> 01:24:25,440
No, shut them all down. Hurry! Oh, no.

981
01:24:37,080 --> 01:24:38,560
What?

982
01:24:39,600 --> 01:24:41,400
You did great, 3PO!

983
01:24:41,920 --> 01:24:43,880
Listen to them. They're dying, R2.

984
01:24:43,960 --> 01:24:46,120
Curse my metal body.
I wasn't fast enough.

985
01:24:46,200 --> 01:24:49,280
It's all my fault. My poor master.

986
01:24:49,360 --> 01:24:50,960
We're all right. You did great!

987
01:24:51,960 --> 01:24:54,320
Hey! Open the pressure
maintenance hatch

988
01:24:54,400 --> 01:24:55,800
on unit number... Where are we?

989
01:24:56,320 --> 01:24:59,200
<i>3263827.</i>

990
01:25:45,280 --> 01:25:48,720
If we can avoid any more female advice,
we oughta be able to get out of here.

991
01:25:48,800 --> 01:25:50,480
Let's get moving.

992
01:25:52,240 --> 01:25:54,360
Where you goin'?

993
01:25:54,440 --> 01:25:56,240
Wait! They'll hear!

994
01:25:58,080 --> 01:25:59,440
Come here, you big coward.

995
01:25:59,520 --> 01:26:01,200
-Chewie, come here.
-Listen.

996
01:26:02,080 --> 01:26:04,840
I don't know who you are
or where you came from,

997
01:26:04,920 --> 01:26:07,760
but from now on,
you do as I tell you, okay?

998
01:26:08,640 --> 01:26:11,600
Look, Your Worshipfulness,
let's get one thing straight.

999
01:26:11,680 --> 01:26:14,960
I take orders from just one person. Me.

1000
01:26:15,040 --> 01:26:16,960
It's a wonder you're still alive.

1001
01:26:17,040 --> 01:26:20,280
Will somebody get
this big walking carpet out of my way?

1002
01:26:20,360 --> 01:26:22,600
No reward is worth this.

1003
01:26:32,800 --> 01:26:34,760
Give me regular reports, please.

1004
01:26:34,880 --> 01:26:35,960
Right.

1005
01:26:38,120 --> 01:26:41,400
-Do you know what's going on?
-Maybe it's another drill.

1006
01:26:46,400 --> 01:26:48,440
You seen that new VT-16?

1007
01:26:48,560 --> 01:26:50,480
Yeah. Some of the other guys
were telling me about it.

1008
01:26:50,560 --> 01:26:52,800
They say it's quite a thing to see.

1009
01:26:52,880 --> 01:26:55,080
What was that?

1010
01:26:55,160 --> 01:26:58,440
It's nothing. Outgassing.
Don't worry about it.

1011
01:27:03,440 --> 01:27:05,560
-There she is.
-C-3PO, do you copy?

1012
01:27:05,640 --> 01:27:06,640
<i>Yes, sir.</i>

1013
01:27:06,720 --> 01:27:08,600
-Are you safe?
<i>-For the moment.</i>

1014
01:27:09,120 --> 01:27:10,960
We're in the main hangar
across from the ship.

1015
01:27:13,320 --> 01:27:14,640
We're right above you. Stand by.

1016
01:27:15,160 --> 01:27:17,720
You came in that thing?
You're braver than I thought.

1017
01:27:17,840 --> 01:27:19,840
Nice. Come on.

1018
01:27:23,480 --> 01:27:24,880
It's them. Blast them.

1019
01:27:26,640 --> 01:27:27,680
Get back to the ship!

1020
01:27:27,760 --> 01:27:29,960
-Where are you going?
-He certainly has courage.

1021
01:27:30,040 --> 01:27:33,160
What good will it do us
if he gets himself killed? Come on.

1022
01:27:58,640 --> 01:28:00,640
I think we took a wrong turn.

1023
01:28:05,560 --> 01:28:06,640
There's no lock.

1024
01:28:10,880 --> 01:28:13,560
-That oughta hold them for a while.
-Quick. We've got to get across.

1025
01:28:13,640 --> 01:28:16,960
-Find the controls to extend the bridge.
-I think I just blasted it.

1026
01:28:17,040 --> 01:28:18,680
They're coming through.

1027
01:28:41,040 --> 01:28:42,680
Here, hold this.

1028
01:28:59,440 --> 01:29:00,600
Here they come.

1029
01:29:11,440 --> 01:29:12,960
For luck.

1030
01:29:19,120 --> 01:29:23,840
We think they may be splitting up.
They may be on Level 5 and 6 now, sir.

1031
01:29:37,960 --> 01:29:39,960
Where could they be?

1032
01:29:44,080 --> 01:29:45,640
Close the blast doors.

1033
01:29:52,800 --> 01:29:55,240
Open the blast doors.
Open the blast doors.

1034
01:30:13,520 --> 01:30:19,040
I've been waiting for you, Obi-Wan.
We meet again at last.

1035
01:30:19,120 --> 01:30:20,840
The circle is now complete.

1036
01:30:21,160 --> 01:30:23,120
When I left you, I was but the learner.

1037
01:30:23,200 --> 01:30:25,600
Now I am the master.

1038
01:30:25,680 --> 01:30:28,000
Only a master of evil, Darth.

1039
01:30:48,000 --> 01:30:50,280
Your powers are weak, old man.

1040
01:30:50,960 --> 01:30:54,120
You can't win, Darth.
If you strike me down,

1041
01:30:54,200 --> 01:30:57,600
I shall become more powerful
than you can possibly imagine.

1042
01:31:04,920 --> 01:31:07,000
You should not have come back.

1043
01:31:32,720 --> 01:31:34,360
Didn't we just leave this party?

1044
01:31:37,120 --> 01:31:39,640
-What kept you?
-We ran into some old friends.

1045
01:31:39,720 --> 01:31:42,040
-The ship all right?
-Seems okay, if we can get to it.

1046
01:31:42,120 --> 01:31:44,080
I hope the old man got
the tractor beam down.

1047
01:31:59,440 --> 01:32:00,640
Look.

1048
01:32:03,600 --> 01:32:05,560
Come on, R2. We're going.

1049
01:32:07,240 --> 01:32:08,320
Now's our chance. Go!

1050
01:32:38,480 --> 01:32:39,640
Come on!

1051
01:32:40,600 --> 01:32:42,200
Come on!

1052
01:32:42,280 --> 01:32:45,360
-Luke, it's too late!
-Blast the door, kid!

1053
01:32:55,040 --> 01:32:56,520
<i>Run, Luke, run.</i>

1054
01:33:00,480 --> 01:33:02,160
I hope that old man got
the tractor beam down,

1055
01:33:02,240 --> 01:33:04,080
or this is gonna be a short trip. Hit it!

1056
01:33:36,520 --> 01:33:38,440
We're coming up on their sentry ships.

1057
01:33:38,520 --> 01:33:40,120
Hold them off.
Angle the deflector shields

1058
01:33:40,200 --> 01:33:42,040
while I charge up the main guns.

1059
01:33:51,080 --> 01:33:53,080
I can't believe he's gone.

1060
01:33:57,040 --> 01:33:58,520
There wasn't anything
you could have done.

1061
01:33:59,560 --> 01:34:01,520
Come on, buddy.
We're not out of this yet.

1062
01:34:18,360 --> 01:34:20,760
You in, kid? Okay, stay sharp.

1063
01:34:31,600 --> 01:34:32,720
Here they come.

1064
01:34:50,720 --> 01:34:52,560
They're coming in too fast!

1065
01:35:00,560 --> 01:35:04,400
-We've lost the lateral controls.
-Don't worry. She'll hold together.

1066
01:35:06,080 --> 01:35:08,000
Hear me, baby? Hold together.

1067
01:35:30,000 --> 01:35:31,840
Got him. I got him!

1068
01:35:31,920 --> 01:35:34,120
Great, kid. Don't get cocky.

1069
01:35:35,320 --> 01:35:37,120
There's still two more.

1070
01:36:10,960 --> 01:36:13,800
-That's it. We did it.
-We did it.

1071
01:36:14,760 --> 01:36:17,320
Help. I think I'm melting.
This is all your fault.

1072
01:36:25,320 --> 01:36:26,800
Are they away?

1073
01:36:26,880 --> 01:36:29,800
They've just made the jump
into hyperspace.

1074
01:36:29,880 --> 01:36:33,280
You're sure the homing beacon
is secure aboard their ship?

1075
01:36:34,480 --> 01:36:37,080
I'm taking an awful risk, Vader.

1076
01:36:37,160 --> 01:36:38,800
This had better work.

1077
01:36:39,600 --> 01:36:41,840
Not a bad bit of rescuing, huh?

1078
01:36:41,920 --> 01:36:44,960
You know,
sometimes I amaze even myself.

1079
01:36:45,320 --> 01:36:47,480
That doesn't sound too hard.

1080
01:36:47,560 --> 01:36:51,520
They let us go. It's the only
explanation for the ease of our escape.

1081
01:36:51,600 --> 01:36:54,400
-You call that easy?
-They're tracking us.

1082
01:36:54,480 --> 01:36:55,880
Not this ship, sister.

1083
01:36:57,200 --> 01:36:59,920
At least the information in R2
is still intact.

1084
01:37:00,000 --> 01:37:02,280
What's so important?
What's he carrying?

1085
01:37:02,360 --> 01:37:05,480
The technical readouts
of that battle station.

1086
01:37:05,560 --> 01:37:08,880
I only hope that when the data's
analyzed a weakness can be found.

1087
01:37:08,960 --> 01:37:12,320
-It's not over yet.
-It is for me, sister.

1088
01:37:12,400 --> 01:37:15,960
I ain't in this for your revolution,
and I'm not in it for you, Princess.

1089
01:37:16,040 --> 01:37:18,920
I expect to be well paid.
I'm in it for the money.

1090
01:37:19,000 --> 01:37:21,040
You needn't worry about your reward.

1091
01:37:21,120 --> 01:37:24,040
If money is all that you love,
then that's what you'll receive.

1092
01:37:27,200 --> 01:37:29,200
Your friend is quite a mercenary.

1093
01:37:29,280 --> 01:37:32,480
I wonder if he really cares
about anything or anybody.

1094
01:37:33,720 --> 01:37:35,240
I care.

1095
01:37:41,680 --> 01:37:43,320
So...

1096
01:37:43,880 --> 01:37:45,600
What do you think of her, Han?

1097
01:37:45,680 --> 01:37:47,280
I'm trying not to, kid.

1098
01:37:48,400 --> 01:37:49,400
Good.

1099
01:37:53,320 --> 01:37:55,680
Still, she's got a lot of spirit.

1100
01:37:58,320 --> 01:38:00,920
What do you think? You think
a princess and a guy like me...

1101
01:38:01,000 --> 01:38:02,000
No.

1102
01:38:49,440 --> 01:38:52,480
You're safe. When we heard about
Alderaan, we feared the worst.

1103
01:38:52,560 --> 01:38:54,480
We have no time for sorrows,
Commander.

1104
01:38:54,560 --> 01:38:57,600
You must use the information
in this R2 unit to help plan the attack.

1105
01:38:57,680 --> 01:38:59,640
It's our only hope.

1106
01:39:20,760 --> 01:39:23,440
-Yes.
<i>-We're approaching the planet Yavin.</i>

1107
01:39:23,560 --> 01:39:25,880
<i>The rebel base is on a moon</i>
<i>on the far side.</i>

1108
01:39:25,960 --> 01:39:27,960
<i>We are preparing to orbit the planet.</i>

1109
01:39:36,960 --> 01:39:39,040
The battle station is heavily shielded

1110
01:39:39,160 --> 01:39:42,600
and carries a firepower
greater than half the starfleet.

1111
01:39:43,320 --> 01:39:47,400
Its defenses are designed around
a direct large-scale assault.

1112
01:39:48,040 --> 01:39:52,720
A small, one-man fighter should be able
to penetrate the outer defense.

1113
01:39:54,480 --> 01:39:55,600
Pardon me for asking, sir,

1114
01:39:55,720 --> 01:39:58,320
but what good are snub fighters
against that?

1115
01:39:58,400 --> 01:40:03,000
The Empire doesn't consider a small,
one-man fighter to be any threat

1116
01:40:03,080 --> 01:40:05,800
or they'd have a tighter defense.

1117
01:40:05,880 --> 01:40:09,160
An analysis of the plans
provided by Princess Leia

1118
01:40:09,240 --> 01:40:12,360
has demonstrated a weakness
in the battle station.

1119
01:40:13,200 --> 01:40:15,200
The approach will not be easy.

1120
01:40:15,800 --> 01:40:18,400
You're required to maneuver
straight down this trench

1121
01:40:18,480 --> 01:40:21,120
and skim the surface to this point.

1122
01:40:21,920 --> 01:40:24,760
The target area is only two meters wide.

1123
01:40:24,840 --> 01:40:28,440
It's a small thermal exhaust port
right below the main port.

1124
01:40:30,000 --> 01:40:32,880
The shaft leads directly
to the reactor system.

1125
01:40:32,960 --> 01:40:35,680
A precise hit will start a chain reaction

1126
01:40:35,800 --> 01:40:38,040
which should destroy the station.

1127
01:40:38,120 --> 01:40:41,640
Only a precise hit will
set up a chain reaction.

1128
01:40:41,720 --> 01:40:44,880
The shaft is ray-shielded,
so you'll have to use proton torpedoes.

1129
01:40:45,360 --> 01:40:47,120
That's impossible, even for a computer.

1130
01:40:47,200 --> 01:40:51,040
No, it's not. I used to bull's-eye
womp rats in my T-16 back home.

1131
01:40:51,120 --> 01:40:53,560
They're not much bigger
than two meters.

1132
01:40:53,640 --> 01:40:56,760
Then man your ships,
and may the Force be with you.

1133
01:41:05,040 --> 01:41:07,600
<i>Orbiting the planet</i>
<i>at maximum velocity.</i>

1134
01:41:08,280 --> 01:41:12,200
<i>The moon with the rebel base</i>
<i>will be in range in 30 minutes.</i>

1135
01:41:12,280 --> 01:41:14,720
This will be a day long remembered.

1136
01:41:14,840 --> 01:41:16,800
It has seen the end of Kenobi

1137
01:41:16,880 --> 01:41:19,960
and will soon see
the end of the rebellion.

1138
01:41:25,200 --> 01:41:28,480
<i>All flight crews, man your stations.</i>

1139
01:41:33,920 --> 01:41:37,040
So, you got your reward
and you're just leaving, then?

1140
01:41:37,120 --> 01:41:39,120
That's right. Yeah.

1141
01:41:40,240 --> 01:41:42,840
I got some old debts
I gotta pay off with this stuff.

1142
01:41:42,920 --> 01:41:44,760
Even if I didn't,
you don't think I'd be fool enough

1143
01:41:44,840 --> 01:41:47,040
to stick around here, do ya?

1144
01:41:47,600 --> 01:41:49,000
Why don't you come with us?

1145
01:41:49,080 --> 01:41:50,880
You're pretty good in a fight.
We could use ya.

1146
01:41:51,000 --> 01:41:53,840
Come on.
Why don't you take a look around?

1147
01:41:53,920 --> 01:41:56,600
You know what's about to happen,
what they're up against.

1148
01:41:56,720 --> 01:41:59,480
They could use a good pilot like you.
You're turning your back on them.

1149
01:42:00,080 --> 01:42:02,000
What good's a reward
if you ain't around to use it?

1150
01:42:02,480 --> 01:42:05,280
Besides, attacking that battle station
ain't my idea of courage.

1151
01:42:05,360 --> 01:42:08,000
It's more like suicide.

1152
01:42:09,840 --> 01:42:12,680
All right.
Well, take care of yourself, Han.

1153
01:42:12,760 --> 01:42:15,400
I guess that's what you're best at,
isn't it?

1154
01:42:15,760 --> 01:42:16,840
Hey, Luke.

1155
01:42:20,160 --> 01:42:22,520
May the Force be with you.

1156
01:42:29,040 --> 01:42:32,640
What are you looking at?
I know what I'm doing.

1157
01:42:36,640 --> 01:42:39,120
<i>All pilots to your stations.</i>

1158
01:42:47,760 --> 01:42:50,320
-What's wrong?
-It's Han.

1159
01:42:50,400 --> 01:42:52,880
I don't know.
I really thought he'd change his mind.

1160
01:42:52,960 --> 01:42:56,520
He's got to follow his own path.
No one can choose it for him.

1161
01:42:57,520 --> 01:43:00,320
I only wish Ben were here.

1162
01:43:08,000 --> 01:43:10,880
<i>Open main launch tubes.</i>

1163
01:43:10,960 --> 01:43:12,880
<i>Main launch tubes opening, sir.</i>

1164
01:43:13,000 --> 01:43:14,680
Hey, Luke!

1165
01:43:14,760 --> 01:43:17,960
-Biggs!
-I don't believe it. How are ya?

1166
01:43:18,040 --> 01:43:20,120
-Coming up?
-I'll be up there with you.

1167
01:43:20,200 --> 01:43:22,760
-Have I got stories to tell you.
-Skywalker.

1168
01:43:24,320 --> 01:43:25,840
Are you sure you can handle this ship?

1169
01:43:25,920 --> 01:43:29,720
Sir, Luke is the best bush pilot
in the outer-rim territories.

1170
01:43:30,320 --> 01:43:32,880
-You'll do all right.
-Thank you, sir. I'll try.

1171
01:43:32,960 --> 01:43:36,880
Gotta get aboard. We'll hear all your
stories when we get back, all right?

1172
01:43:36,960 --> 01:43:39,680
Hey, Biggs.
I told you I'd make it someday.

1173
01:43:39,760 --> 01:43:42,760
It'll be like old times, Luke.
They'll never stop us.

1174
01:43:45,640 --> 01:43:48,600
This R2 unit of yours seems
a bit beat up. You want a new one?

1175
01:43:49,160 --> 01:43:51,800
Not on your life. That droid and I
have been through a lot.

1176
01:43:51,880 --> 01:43:52,960
You okay, R2?

1177
01:43:54,560 --> 01:43:56,000
Good.

1178
01:43:57,040 --> 01:44:00,400
<i>Gold squadron,</i>
<i>begin takeoff procedure.</i>

1179
01:44:00,480 --> 01:44:03,440
Hang on tight, R2.
You've got to come back.

1180
01:44:05,320 --> 01:44:07,320
You wouldn't want my life
to get boring, would you?

1181
01:44:56,160 --> 01:44:59,160
<i>Luke, the Force will be with you.</i>

1182
01:45:10,920 --> 01:45:14,240
<i>Standby alert. Death Star approaching.</i>

1183
01:45:14,320 --> 01:45:17,480
<i>Estimated time to firing range,</i>
<i>15 minutes.</i>

1184
01:45:30,560 --> 01:45:32,880
-All wings report in.
-Red 10 standing by.

1185
01:45:32,960 --> 01:45:35,200
<i>-Red Seven standing by.</i>
-Red Three standing by.

1186
01:45:35,280 --> 01:45:38,040
-Red Six standing by.
<i>-Red Nine standing by.</i>

1187
01:45:38,120 --> 01:45:40,120
-Red Two standing by.
<i>-Red 11 standing by.</i>

1188
01:45:40,200 --> 01:45:42,160
Red Five standing by.

1189
01:45:43,520 --> 01:45:45,440
Lock S-foils in attack position.

1190
01:45:49,680 --> 01:45:51,720
<i>We're passing</i>
<i>through the magnetic field.</i>

1191
01:45:51,800 --> 01:45:54,600
Hold tight. Switch your deflectors on.

1192
01:45:54,680 --> 01:45:56,120
<i>Double front.</i>

1193
01:45:59,120 --> 01:46:00,640
Look at the size of that thing.

1194
01:46:00,720 --> 01:46:03,560
Cut the chatter, Red Two.
Accelerate to attack speed.

1195
01:46:07,000 --> 01:46:09,800
-This is it, boys.
-Red Leader, this is Gold Leader.

1196
01:46:09,880 --> 01:46:12,760
<i>-I copy, Gold Leader.</i>
-We're starting for the target shaft.

1197
01:46:12,840 --> 01:46:16,280
We're in position. I'm going to cut
across the axis and draw their fire.

1198
01:46:30,680 --> 01:46:33,960
<i>-Heavy fire, boss, 23 degrees.</i>
<i>-I see it. Stay low.</i>

1199
01:46:41,400 --> 01:46:43,000
This is Red Five. I'm going in.

1200
01:46:47,480 --> 01:46:48,480
<i>Luke, pull up!</i>

1201
01:46:50,400 --> 01:46:52,480
-You all right?
-A little cooked, but I'm okay.

1202
01:46:58,480 --> 01:47:02,400
We count 30 rebel ships, but they're so
small they're evading our turbolasers.

1203
01:47:02,520 --> 01:47:04,440
We'll have to destroy them ship to ship.

1204
01:47:04,520 --> 01:47:06,600
Get the crews to their fighters.

1205
01:47:09,160 --> 01:47:11,000
Watch yourself. There's a lot of fire

1206
01:47:11,080 --> 01:47:13,360
coming from
the right side of that deflection tower.

1207
01:47:13,440 --> 01:47:14,440
I'm on it.

1208
01:47:14,520 --> 01:47:17,920
-I'm going in. Cover me, Porkins.
-Right with you, Red Three.

1209
01:47:24,280 --> 01:47:26,120
I've got a problem here.

1210
01:47:26,200 --> 01:47:27,600
-Eject.
-I can hold it.

1211
01:47:27,680 --> 01:47:29,880
-Pull up!
-No, I'm all right...

1212
01:47:34,040 --> 01:47:37,680
<i>The rebel base will be in firing range</i>
<i>in seven minutes.</i>

1213
01:47:40,880 --> 01:47:43,760
<i>Luke, trust your feelings.</i>

1214
01:47:51,680 --> 01:47:53,320
Squad leaders,

1215
01:47:53,400 --> 01:47:55,520
we've picked up a new group of signals.

1216
01:47:55,600 --> 01:47:57,200
Enemy fighters coming your way.

1217
01:47:57,280 --> 01:47:58,960
My scope's negative.
I don't see anything.

1218
01:47:59,040 --> 01:48:01,240
-Pick up your visual scanning.
<i>-Here they come.</i>

1219
01:48:04,480 --> 01:48:06,240
You've got one on your tail.

1220
01:48:11,560 --> 01:48:12,600
I'm hit!

1221
01:48:13,920 --> 01:48:16,400
-You've picked one up. Watch it.
-I can't see it.

1222
01:48:18,400 --> 01:48:20,160
He's on me tight. I can't shake him.

1223
01:48:22,080 --> 01:48:24,160
I'll be right there.

1224
01:48:36,080 --> 01:48:39,520
Several fighters have broken off
from the main group. Come with me.

1225
01:48:42,960 --> 01:48:46,120
<i>-Fall in. Fall in.</i>
<i>-Watch your back, Luke.</i>

1226
01:48:46,760 --> 01:48:48,400
<i>Fighters above you, coming in.</i>

1227
01:48:54,800 --> 01:48:57,520
I'm hit, but not bad.
R2, see what you can do with it.

1228
01:48:57,600 --> 01:48:59,800
<i>Hang on back there.</i>

1229
01:49:00,360 --> 01:49:02,560
<i>Red Six, can you see Red Five?</i>

1230
01:49:02,640 --> 01:49:05,040
<i>There's a heavy fire zone.</i>
<i>Red Five, where are you?</i>

1231
01:49:05,440 --> 01:49:06,880
I can't shake him.

1232
01:49:10,560 --> 01:49:12,120
I'm on him, Luke.

1233
01:49:15,320 --> 01:49:16,960
Blast it, Biggs. Where are you?

1234
01:49:24,200 --> 01:49:26,760
<i>-Thanks, Wedge.</i>
<i>-Good shooting, Wedge.</i>

1235
01:49:26,840 --> 01:49:30,000
<i>Red Leader, this is Gold Leader.</i>
<i>We're starting our attack run.</i>

1236
01:49:31,840 --> 01:49:34,160
<i>I copy, Gold Leader.</i>
<i>Move into position.</i>

1237
01:49:36,560 --> 01:49:38,920
Stay in attack formation.

1238
01:49:39,000 --> 01:49:41,840
<i>The exhaust port</i>
<i>is marked and locked in.</i>

1239
01:49:47,680 --> 01:49:50,840
Switch all power
to front deflector screen.

1240
01:49:50,920 --> 01:49:54,160
Switch all power
to front deflector screen.

1241
01:49:58,840 --> 01:50:00,640
How many guns do you think,
Gold Five?

1242
01:50:00,720 --> 01:50:03,960
<i>Say about 20 guns, some on</i>
<i>the surface, some on the towers.</i>

1243
01:50:04,080 --> 01:50:06,840
<i>Death Star will be in range</i>
<i>in five minutes.</i>

1244
01:50:09,040 --> 01:50:12,040
Switch to targeting computer.

1245
01:50:14,520 --> 01:50:16,520
Computer's locked. Getting a signal.

1246
01:50:18,880 --> 01:50:21,040
The guns. They've stopped.

1247
01:50:22,720 --> 01:50:25,520
Stabilize your rear deflectors.
Watch for enemy fighters.

1248
01:50:25,600 --> 01:50:27,800
<i>They're coming in. Three marks at 210.</i>

1249
01:50:30,040 --> 01:50:31,960
I'll take them myself. Cover me.

1250
01:50:32,040 --> 01:50:33,360
Yes, sir.

1251
01:50:47,840 --> 01:50:50,360
-It's no good. I can't maneuver.
-Stay on target.

1252
01:50:50,440 --> 01:50:52,320
-We're too close.
-Stay on target.

1253
01:50:54,120 --> 01:50:55,120
Loosen up!

1254
01:50:58,080 --> 01:51:00,960
Gold Five to Red Leader,
lost Tiree, lost Hutch.

1255
01:51:01,040 --> 01:51:03,400
-I copy, Gold Leader.
-They came from behind.

1256
01:51:09,760 --> 01:51:12,400
We've analyzed their attack, sir,
and there is a danger.

1257
01:51:12,480 --> 01:51:14,400
Should I have your ship standing by?

1258
01:51:14,480 --> 01:51:17,360
Evacuate? In our moment of triumph?

1259
01:51:17,440 --> 01:51:19,920
I think you overestimate their chances.

1260
01:51:20,600 --> 01:51:22,640
<i>Rebel base, three minutes and closing.</i>

1261
01:51:23,640 --> 01:51:25,280
Red boys, this is Red Leader.

1262
01:51:25,360 --> 01:51:27,040
<i>Rendezvous at mark 6.1.</i>

1263
01:51:27,160 --> 01:51:30,960
<i>-This is Red Two flying toward you.</i>
<i>-Red Three standing by.</i>

1264
01:51:31,040 --> 01:51:32,720
Red Leader, this is Base One.

1265
01:51:32,800 --> 01:51:35,480
<i>Keep half your group out of range</i>
<i>for the next run.</i>

1266
01:51:35,560 --> 01:51:38,200
<i>Copy, Base One.</i>
<i>Luke, take Red Two and Three.</i>

1267
01:51:38,280 --> 01:51:41,600
Hold up here and wait for
my signal to start your run.

1268
01:51:50,240 --> 01:51:51,520
This is it.

1269
01:51:55,840 --> 01:51:56,920
We should be able to see it by now.

1270
01:51:59,640 --> 01:52:01,400
Keep your eyes open for those fighters.

1271
01:52:03,200 --> 01:52:05,600
There's too much interference.
Red Five, can you see them?

1272
01:52:05,680 --> 01:52:08,680
-No sign of any... Wait. Coming in .35.
-I see them.

1273
01:52:10,200 --> 01:52:11,320
I'm in range.

1274
01:52:12,560 --> 01:52:13,560
Target's coming up.

1275
01:52:16,880 --> 01:52:19,040
Just hold them off for a few seconds.

1276
01:52:19,880 --> 01:52:21,480
Close up formation.

1277
01:52:23,200 --> 01:52:24,840
Almost there.

1278
01:52:34,040 --> 01:52:37,360
-Let her loose. They're right behind me.
-Almost there.

1279
01:52:38,720 --> 01:52:40,400
I can't hold them.

1280
01:52:48,360 --> 01:52:49,400
It's away!

1281
01:52:53,840 --> 01:52:55,480
<i>-It's a hit!</i>
<i>-Negative.</i>

1282
01:52:55,560 --> 01:52:57,640
Negative. It didn't go in.

1283
01:52:57,720 --> 01:53:00,400
<i>It just impacted on the surface.</i>

1284
01:53:06,880 --> 01:53:07,960
<i>Red Leader, we're right above you.</i>

1285
01:53:08,040 --> 01:53:10,800
Turn to .05. We'll cover for you.

1286
01:53:10,880 --> 01:53:13,800
<i>Stay there. I just lost</i>
<i>my starboard engine.</i>

1287
01:53:14,600 --> 01:53:16,880
Get set up for your attack run.

1288
01:53:30,240 --> 01:53:32,800
<i>Rebel base, one minute and closing.</i>

1289
01:53:33,560 --> 01:53:35,160
<i>Biggs, Wedge, let's close it up.</i>

1290
01:53:35,240 --> 01:53:38,600
<i>We're going in full throttle. That ought</i>
<i>to keep those fighters off our back.</i>

1291
01:53:38,680 --> 01:53:39,680
Right with you, boss.

1292
01:53:40,920 --> 01:53:43,200
At that speed,
will you be able to pull out in time?

1293
01:53:43,280 --> 01:53:45,280
It'll be just like
Beggars Canyon back home.

1294
01:53:52,640 --> 01:53:54,920
We'll stay back far enough to cover you.

1295
01:53:55,000 --> 01:53:57,560
<i>My scope shows the tower,</i>
<i>but I can't see the exhaust port.</i>

1296
01:53:57,640 --> 01:53:59,080
Are you sure the computer can hit it?

1297
01:54:02,600 --> 01:54:04,600
Watch yourself.
Increase speed, full throttle.

1298
01:54:04,680 --> 01:54:05,960
What about that tower?

1299
01:54:06,040 --> 01:54:08,480
You worry about those fighters.
I'll worry about the tower.

1300
01:54:14,840 --> 01:54:18,480
R2, that stabilizer's broken loose
again. See if you can't lock it down.

1301
01:54:27,640 --> 01:54:29,440
<i>Fighters coming in .3.</i>

1302
01:54:38,320 --> 01:54:40,880
<i>-I'm hit. I can't stay with you.</i>
<i>-Get clear, Wedge.</i>

1303
01:54:40,960 --> 01:54:42,120
You can't do any more good back there.

1304
01:54:42,200 --> 01:54:43,480
Sorry.

1305
01:54:44,520 --> 01:54:46,480
Let him go. Stay on the leader.

1306
01:54:49,400 --> 01:54:51,640
Hurry, Luke.
They're coming in much faster this time.

1307
01:54:55,800 --> 01:54:57,040
R2, try and increase the power.

1308
01:55:03,840 --> 01:55:05,160
<i>Hurry up, Luke. Quick.</i>

1309
01:55:06,040 --> 01:55:07,200
Quick.

1310
01:55:14,200 --> 01:55:16,800
<i>Rebel base, 30 seconds and closing.</i>

1311
01:55:16,880 --> 01:55:18,000
I'm on the leader.

1312
01:55:21,440 --> 01:55:22,920
Hang on, R2.

1313
01:55:38,760 --> 01:55:41,360
<i>Use the Force, Luke.</i>

1314
01:55:44,120 --> 01:55:46,160
<i>Let go, Luke.</i>

1315
01:55:47,840 --> 01:55:50,040
The Force is strong with this one.

1316
01:55:50,120 --> 01:55:52,080
<i>Luke, trust me.</i>

1317
01:55:57,240 --> 01:55:59,080
<i>His computer's off.</i>

1318
01:55:59,160 --> 01:56:01,280
<i>You switched off your</i>
<i>targeting computer. What's wrong?</i>

1319
01:56:01,360 --> 01:56:04,040
<i>Nothing. I'm all right.</i>

1320
01:56:17,240 --> 01:56:18,480
<i>I've lost R2.</i>

1321
01:56:19,920 --> 01:56:22,200
<i>The Death Star has cleared the planet.</i>

1322
01:56:22,280 --> 01:56:24,600
<i>The Death Star has cleared the planet.</i>

1323
01:56:25,640 --> 01:56:27,280
<i>Rebel base in range.</i>

1324
01:56:27,360 --> 01:56:29,280
You may fire when ready.

1325
01:56:30,000 --> 01:56:31,440
<i>Commence primary ignition.</i>

1326
01:56:45,440 --> 01:56:46,840
I have you now.

1327
01:56:49,280 --> 01:56:50,480
What?

1328
01:56:53,080 --> 01:56:54,120
Look out.

1329
01:57:00,760 --> 01:57:03,600
You're all clear, kid.
Now let's blow this thing and go home.

1330
01:57:10,440 --> 01:57:12,080
<i>Stand by.</i>

1331
01:57:15,440 --> 01:57:17,160
<i>Stand by.</i>

1332
01:57:26,960 --> 01:57:28,880
Great shot, kid!
That was one in a million!

1333
01:57:30,320 --> 01:57:34,800
<i>Remember, the Force</i>
<i>will be with you always.</i>

1334
01:58:00,400 --> 01:58:02,040
I just knew you'd come back.

1335
01:58:02,120 --> 01:58:04,680
I wasn't gonna let you get all
the credit and take all the reward.

1336
01:58:04,760 --> 01:58:07,080
I knew there was more to you
than money.

1337
01:58:07,600 --> 01:58:08,680
Oh, no.

1338
01:58:08,760 --> 01:58:11,200
Oh, my. R2, can you hear me?

1339
01:58:11,880 --> 01:58:14,760
Say something.
You can repair him, can't you?

1340
01:58:14,840 --> 01:58:18,080
-We'll get to work on him right away.
-You must repair him.

1341
01:58:18,160 --> 01:58:21,120
Sir, if any of my circuits or gears
will help, I'll gladly donate them.

1342
01:58:21,200 --> 01:58:23,200
He'll be all right.

1343
02:04:39,720 --> 02:04:40,720
English -US

